title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick, then add sliced apples to mixture and pour in shell.

title: mom's apple frosting
directions: Mix grated apple with sugar and egg white.
Beat until stiff and white.
(If apple yellows it will whiten when beaten.)

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Form balls.
Freeze 1 hour.
Meanwhile melt the chocolate chips and 1/8 pound paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and set on wax paper.
Use toothpick to dip.
Cover holes by drizzling small amount of chocolate from spoon.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar and margarine. Beat at medium speed until creamy, 1 to 2 minutes. Continue beating, adding eggs, one at a time, until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes. Add cheese, light sour cream, corn, chilies and onion powder.
Continue beating, scraping bowl often until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Continue beating until just mixed, 1 minute.
Pour batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cranberry-apple ketchup
directions: In a large saucepan, using a wire whisk, whip cranberry sauce. Then add the remaining ingredients.
Place over medium heat, whisking occasionally until smooth, and flavors are blended, about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour into gift bottle or jars and cover.
Refrigerate up to one month.
This is very good served with turkey, pork or game.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put bread in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Scald milk and butter. Mix eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in bowl and blend milk with it. Pour over the bread and stir it in the baking dish.
Stir in the raisins.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water 1-inch deep.
Bake until silver knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Serve warm.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: aunt pat's chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Combine and mix other ingredients; add chicken and make sure all chicken is covered with sauce.
Put in casserole or oblong baking dish, cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before baking at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove from baking dish to serving platter and pour remaining sauce over chicken.

title: ruth's lake texoma beans
directions: Saute onion in a little oil.
Brown the meat.
Mix all the ingredients except the beans.
Place beans in a crock-pot.
Cover with water.
Add the meat mixture and stir well.
Turn the crock-pot on high.
Go fishing for about 6 hours.
Come home and make cornbread and supper is ready.

title: spiced applesauce bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice.
Stir into applesauce mixture; beat well.
Fold in the 1/2 cup chopped pecans and turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine the 1/4 cup pecans, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: tea punch
directions: Add sugar and limeade to tea.
Then add enough pineapple juice to complete the gallon.
Stir.
Pour Tea Punch over ice and serve.

title: butter-praline cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: rice krispies
directions: Mix together sugar and syrup, boil and add peanut butter. Pour into large bowl with rice krispies. Press into buttered pan. Prepare topping: Melt both chips and spread on top of bars.

title: cheese cake supreme
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice and salt, mixing until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: supper layer casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown onion and fat.
Add meat and brown.
Pour soup and milk over meat mix.
Put 1/2 macaroni in casserole and 1/2 cup green beans or asparagus and 1/2 meat mix.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and repeat process.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: slow-cooker enchiladas
directions: In a skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until beef is browned and vegetables are tender; drain. Add the next eight ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Combine cheeses. In a 5 qt. slow cooker, layer about 3/4 c. beef mixture, one tortilla and about 1/3 c. cheese. Repeat layers. Cover and cook on low for 5-7 hours or until heated through.

title: sandbag oven stew
directions: Place ingredients in Dutch oven.
Mix well and cover.
Cook in a 250° oven for 6 to 8 hours.
Don't open until ready!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender, best peeled and chopped for this. Drain almost all the liquid and let it cool a little while.
Saute the onion in butter and add the celery, pimentos and soup. Crumble cornbread in bowl and add egg and milk.
Add eggplant, onion and etc. from skillet and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes in 400° oven.
Sprinkle top with cheese and let it melt in the heat of the dish.

title: miss ruby's burnt sugar frosting
directions: Melt 1/2 cup sugar in heavy pot over medium heat.
In another boiler, combine 2 1/2 cups sugar and the flour, then add milk and margarine (cut up).
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour this boiling mixture into melted sugar; stir until well mixed.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool, add vanilla and beat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: carolyn's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball.
You can add more chopped beef on top to garnish.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients. Grease large baking dish.
Place a layer of tortillas and a layer of meat mixture until all meat mixture is used, with meat on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Longer if you want it thicker.)
When done, top with grated cheese.

title: copper pennies
directions: Stir together carrots, onion and peppers.
All other ingredients, mix together in separate bowl and pour over the carrots.
Chill overnight.
Serve cold.

title: e-z bake beans
directions: Remove fat from can.
Mix everything together.
Bake, covered, at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Continue baking for 15 minutes.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by large rounded spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable appetizer
directions: Cut all ingredients into bite size pieces.
Pour buttermilk salad dressing over all.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Place cut up chicken on top of rice and soup, skin side up.
Mix chicken soup with water and pour over all.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken tests done.

title: sweet and sour pork(microwave)
directions: Place pork loin cubes in a medium casserole dish. Cook, covered, on power 4 for 18 to 20 minutes, until meat is no longer pink. Stir halfway through cooking.

title: great pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan or dish. Sprinkle with the yellow cake mix. Melt 3/4 cup butter. Drizzle over the top of the cake. Top with the walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: sherried chicken and rice
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken, place in cooking pan sprayed with Pam.
Salt and pepper pieces, cook for 1/2 amount of time at 350°. Add sherry to mushroom soup and pour over chicken pieces.
Finish cooking chicken until done.
Serve on rice.

title: coconut pie impossible
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Add sauce and water; boil for 5 minutes. Cut 12 thin slices of Mozzarella and set aside for topping. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spread a little sauce on bottom of baking dish (13 x 9-inch) and arrange a layer of noodles.
Layer cottage cheese mixture, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese until noodles are used up or baking dish is full. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes

title: meatballs(appetizer)
directions: Mix beef with 1/2 cup catsup and 1/2 cup jelly and seasonings. Form into small meatballs.
Simmer in large pot with remaining mixture of catsup and jelly for 1 hour over very low flame. Cover.
Let stand several hours.
Put in fondue dish to keep warm.

title: chocolate walnut dollars
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients and milk.
Melt chocolate (microwave works) and mix into dough.
Dough will be thick.
I knead it with my hands until uniform in color.
Add nuts; divide dough into halves and form into 2 long rolls on plastic wrap.
Chill dough until firm.
Unwrap roll and slice thinly, about 1/2-inch.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Cookies will not puff up. Dough will keep in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 40 half dollar size cookies.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all together at once.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ground beef cordon bleu
directions: Add seasonings to beef; mix well and divide into 8 equal portions.
Form into 8 patties 1/4-inch thick.
Place a slice of bacon on each; add a slice of cheese.
Roll each portion, sealing all edges.
Roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with small amount of oil (or Pam).
Place browned rolls in baking dish.
Pour the cream of mushroom soup over the meat rolls.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with egg noodles, rice or potatoes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put oatmeal and margarine in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over this mixture until the margarine is melted.
Stir in corn syrup and salt.

title: stuffed muffins
directions: Beat 15 strokes.
No more!
Spray muffin tins with nonstick coating.
Add 1/2 butter, then drop teaspoonful of favorite preserves, jelly or apples slices.
Spoon on remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: roast with gravy mix
directions: Turn oven to 350° to 375° (bake).
Put roast in large baking dish; add onion, carrots and potatoes.
Mix gravy mix with water. Mix beef stew mix with water.
Pour over roast.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat and drain, reserving fat in skillet.
Remove meat to 2-quart baking dish.
Saute onion in reserved fat.
Drain off fat and mix onion with meat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until celery is tender. Cover dish for last 1/2 hour of baking.
Serves 6.

title: ham 'n swiss quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate or quiche dish; sprinkle ham, cheese, onion and bell pepper in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on High or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour over ham/cheese mixture. Bake until golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 375° until well browned.

title: delicious vinaigrette for green salads
directions: Place the first four ingredients in a jar.
Add the vinegar and shake well.
Add the oil and shake well again.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Separate celery ribs and cut into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Wash and drain.
Mix cream cheese with finely chopped onion and chopped and drained olives.
Stuff the celery ribs with cream cheese mixture.
Arrange on tray and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef until done.
Drain off grease.
Add to beef, mixed vegetables, rice and soups.
Place in a casserole dish and place in oven for 30 minutes.
Heat oven at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Roll and wrap each chicken breast in one piece of bacon.
Place chip beef in bottom of a baking dish and lay chicken breast on top. Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken breasts.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put all 3 boxes of pudding mixes in a bowl.
Add the milk slowly while using the mixer.
Mix until thick.
Add sour cream and half of the Cool Whip (the
other half goes on top).
Arrange a layer of wafers, then bananas and top with pudding.
Repeat until all of the pudding is used up.
Stand up some wafers around the bowl to make it look better.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix peppers and cucumber in bowl.
Add lemon juice, vinegar, and oregano.
Mix well. Cover and marinate overnight.
Toss well, just before serving and top with crumbled feta cheese.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add bacon, cottage cheese, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate and peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat butter until light and creamy.
Beat in sugars, then eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Beat in peanut butter.
Stir together next four dry ingredients and add to peanut butter mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet about 2-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand on baking sheet few minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake! Leave on cookie sheet for a minute or so before removing.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well the flour, salt and sugar into the shortening.
Beat 1/2 cup plus 1 teaspoon water, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Add to flour mixture and mix until all ingredients are moistened. Makes enough for 2 crusts.

title: apple pie in a glass
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered shaker and shake until well blended.
Pour into tall glass and enjoy!!!

title: parmesan steak
directions: Trim any excess fat from steak; slash remaining fat edge to prevent curling.
Place steak in large shallow dish.
Pour salad dressing over top.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours at room temperature. When ready to cook, preheat broiler.
Place steak on rack in broiler pan.
Brush dressing from dish on top.
Broil 8 inches from heat for 15 minutes.
Turn; broil 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top; broil 5 minutes for rare meat, or until steak is done.
Remove to cutting board; carve into 1/4-inch thick slices. Makes 8 servings.

title: pronto pups
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wieners.
Mix until thin enough for dip batter.
Add more milk, if necessary.
Dip wieners into batter and fry in deep fat until browned.
Drain on towels and serve hot.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper to taste. Coat steak with flour mixture. Brown meat on each side, take out of pan. Make gravy, then add all ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
I usually add 1 large red apple with skin, cut in small pieces, small seedless grapes, several red cherries, cut in small pieces, blot dry.
You can also use a handful of raisins.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and water together, then add 1/2 cake mix, then the other half, then add sour cream. Add lemon extract. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and pack in long dish.

title: hot blackeyed pea dip
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring, until it reaches a boil and cubes are dissolved.
Add peas, tomatoes, garlic and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes;
Combine bacon drippings with flour and stir into peas, then cook 10 minutes more, stirring well; serve hot with corn chips.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put in covered casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water, following label directions; drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly combined. Spread mixture evenly in pan.

title: mrs. coffey's potato scallion soup
directions: Slice onions and dice scallions.
Peel potatoes but leave 20% of skin on.
Boil potatoes with onions.
Cook to desired softness; strain potatoes.
Mash potatoes with all ingredients.
Add more chicken stock if soup is too thick for your taste.

title: citrus honey carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cook in 1-inch boiling water until tender-crisp, about 15 to 20 minutes, then drain.
Blend salt, melted butter, honey and grated peels.
Pour over cooked carrots. Place over low heat until carrots are thoroughly glazed.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch cake pan well.
Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar until blended. Cool.
Stir in egg.
Blend in sifted flour, salt and baking powder mixture.
Mix in vanilla and coconut or nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut in bars while warm.

title: cranberry "tea"(great holiday drink)
directions: Mix together to make concentrate.

title: microwave tomato casserole
directions: Scatter croutons over bottom of a 9-inch glass pie plate. Overlap alternate slices of tomato and Mozzarella cheese on top in a circular pattern to cover.
Sprinkle with basil, chives and pepper.
Microwave uncovered on High 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven; spoon dressing on top.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: skillet beef pilaf
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oil; add meat.
Crumble and let brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add rice and stir over low heat until rice looks translucent (about 3 minutes).
Add broth slowly; cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: grandma ruby's season for gravy
directions: Chop bell peppers, celery, onions, parsley, hot peppers and tomatoes.
Add salt to season.
Cook all ingredients until tender, then cool.
Spoon in plastic ice trays or Ziploc bags and freeze mixture.
If using ice trays, when mixture is frozen, place in Ziploc bags and take out as needed for gravy.

title: very tasty spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour a thin layer of oil into an 8 to 10-quart pot.
Add the onions, peppers, celery and mushrooms.
Using medium heat, saute until tender.
Add garlic; simmer a few moments more.
Remove mixture to a bowl.
Brown the meat in the pot.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Remove tomato cores and bay leaves, if possible.

title: old fashioned stork cake
directions: Cream shortening with molasses.
Add egg.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and beat to a stiff dough.
Roll out to thickness of pie dough.
Cut out with scalloped pie can.	Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.	Put together with sweetened well flavored applesauce.
Makes 9 layers.
Let set a few hours before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, cheese, onion, salt and milk in small casserole dish.
Add potatoes and mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Put all ingredients except soups in casserole.	Pour
soups
over
all and mix.
Cover tightly and heat at 250° for 5 hours.

title: country garden pea salad
directions: Cook peas 5 minutes, then drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients (except tofu) and toss gently.
Blend tofu with some distilled water and pour over salad.
Serve chilled.
Garnish with celery leaves.

title: quick ravioli
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart microwavable casserole. Add onions. Cover loosely and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until beef is no longer pink; drain. Stir in ravioli; cover tightly and microwave 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until hot. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand until cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Make the day before.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Put thawed hash browns in and fluff with a fork.
Melt butter and mix with sour cream, soup and cheese and put on top of potatoes.
Crush one cup of corn flakes and put over the top of this and drizzle butter on corn flakes.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: cheese cake brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop chocolate. In a small saucepan, combine chocolate and butter and melt over low heat, stirring occasionally until smooth.
Let cool.
With mixer at medium-low speed, beat cream cheese and 2/3 cup of sugar until smooth.
Beat in 1 egg, 1 teaspoon of vanilla and the lemon juice; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
On medium-low speed, beat remaining eggs and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla until frothy.
Gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Beat in chocolate mix.
Pour half of chocolate batter into pan.
Carefully spoon on cream cheese mix.
Smooth surface.
Spoon remaining chocolate mix on cheese mix and smooth.
Bake about 1 hour until knife stuck in center comes out clean.
Cool and chill before cutting.

title: quick red pineapple punch
directions: Stir all ingredients together and serve over ice.

title: winter salad pickles
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients in salt water overnight.
Drain in the morning and then add onions.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, sugar and milk.
Wet 6 slices bread; crumble and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: summer trifle
directions: In saucepan mix cornstarch, sugar and eggs until well blended. Gradually stir in milk.
Add butter and stir over medium heat until custard thickens.
Remove from heat and cool, covered.
Stir in vanilla and 1/2 cup almond liqueur.
Cover and chill several hours. Cut cakes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix raspberry preserves with 1/4 cup almond liqueur.
Layer cake cubes, raspberry preserves, peaches and custard in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
End with a drizzle of raspberry preserves.
Chill.
Just before serving, place whipped cream around edge of bowl.
Garnish with peach slices and toasted almonds, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line the pan with crackers.
Mix pudding with milk; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers, then make 2nd layer of crackers and pour remaining pudding over crackers.
Cover with final layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then frost.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Make fluted edge of pastry about 1/2-inch high on rim of pie plate.
Stir pumpkin into eggs.
Blend other ingredients with sugar.
Mix into pumpkin.
Gradually stir in milk until well mixed.
Pour in pastry shell and bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sesame-crisped chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in blender or processor and mix well.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Add chicken and turn several times to coat evenly.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade.
Arrange in single layer in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with crushed breadsticks and dot with butter.
Bake, basting frequently with reserved marinade, until chicken is tender, about 25 minutes. Serve hot.
Can also be made with chicken cutlets.

title: grandma's buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
Set aside; mix wet ingredients.
Blend together; let rise and double size.
Make into rolls.

title: carrot muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs, carrots, cooking oil and lemon juice.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
(Batter should be lumpy.) Fill greased or paper baking cup-lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: frankfurter and corn casserole
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons butter and stir in flour.
Blend thoroughly and add salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in hot milk.
Cook sauce until thick and smooth, stirring.
Remove from heat and add corn. Slowly stir in beaten eggs.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in a preheated moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes. About 15 minutes before dish is done, score frankfurters.
Arrange on top.
Finish baking.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream icing
directions: Mix well, and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked tomato chowder
directions: Grease and flour four 1-cup soup or casserole bowls.
For crust, combine crushed crackers, butter, egg and garlic powder; mix well.
Divide mixture evenly between bowls, pressing to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil and cook chicken 15 minutes.
Take chicken out and bone.
Cut up in small portions.
Use chicken broth to cook noodles.
Bring water to boil; let noodles cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Cook stuffing by directions on box.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and pour cream of chicken soup on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: heluskia
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Brown hamburger, onion and celery in oil.
Add cabbage and steam until tender; do not add water as cabbage will add moisture.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add cooked noodles for the last 5 minutes.
Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: miracle microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in microwave for 2 minutes.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup or more nuts.
Pour on buttered plate or wax paper.
Refrigerate to set.

title: sliced baked potatoes in aluminum box oven(method:  box oven)
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough; otherwise, just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt; drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Place in aluminum box oven.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in large saucepan until vegetables are tender.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups water.
Add bouillon cubes, ketchup, bay leaf and seasoned salt. Heat to boiling, reduce heat and boil gently 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add crabmeat and juice and white fish.
Stir to break up crabmeat.
Boil gently for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Discard bay leaf.
Dissolve dry nonfat milk in remaining 1 1/2 cups water.
Stir into soup.
Reheat to serving temperature. Garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and soda in a large mixing bowl.
Heat margarine, water, cocoa and shortening to boiling.
Pour over flour mixture.
(May mix by hand or mixer.) Add the well beaten eggs, buttermilk and the teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
(Batter is thin.)
Bake 20 minutes in a greased 11 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Let cake cool.

title: quick chicken casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix chicken, celery, onion, nuts, rice, chicken soup, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix mayonnaise with water and add to chicken mixture.
Gently stir in eggs.
Turn into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: prairie state oatmeal cake
directions: In small bowl, combine oats and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In large bowl, beat shortening, sugar and 1 cup brown sugar with electric mixer until combined.
Beat in eggs. Beat in oatmeal mixture.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour and slowly add milk to make a white sauce.
Add seasoning.
Fold sauce into crab meat and spoon into individual greased shells or into casserole.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mom's monster cookies
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed, blending well after each one.
Measure 1/8 cup dough for each cookie.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet and flatten with palm of hand, leaving ample room around each.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Then hide them from Dad and friends.
Recipe may be halved.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together meat and onion.
Dash enough Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, black pepper, lemon pepper and onion salt on top to cover meat; let sit for about 1 hour to marinate and then cook until meatballs are done.

title: chicken in casserole
directions: Mix soups, water and rice in small roaster.
Lay pieces of chicken, skin side up, on mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover pan tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake at 450° for 20 minutes

title: aunt sue's vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix together into large casserole dish.
Add soups, cheese, onion, pepper, sour cream and water to vegetables.

title: peach bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar; mix well.
Add flour, dry jello, coconut and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Mix chopped peaches by hand. Bake in tube or loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° until a toothpick comes out clean.
This bread freezes well.

title: chile con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients in heatproof microwavable bowl.
Serve with tortilla strips or Doritos.

title: coconut frost
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg yolks and vanilla in one pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until thick (about 12 minutes).
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spread in pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Combine dry cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk together.
Add the chopped nuts (optional), stirring by hand. Press 1/2 of cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving juice.
Dice beets.
Add beet juice to vinegar to make 1 cup liquid.
Add sugar and salt to liquid. Bring to a boil.
Pour over jello, stirring until dissolved. Chill until cool.
Add beets, celery and onion.
Chill until set. Spread with Miracle Whip to which you have added a tiny bit of horseradish.
Also good without the horseradish.

title: long johns
directions: Work like bread dough and let rise until double.
Roll out and cut strips.
Let rise again.
Bake.

title: christmas rosettes
directions: Whisk together eggs and whiskey glass of peanut oil until nice and golden yellow.
Add flour, a small amount at a time.
All flour may not be used in mixing dough, but the rest will be used when rolling out dough.
Cut a piece of dough and roll out to be nice and thin.
Then make strips (about 1-inch wide) with a ravioli cutter.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Mix together and bake in 6 greased muffin cups for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pesto pasta chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place chicken in jelly roll pan, 15 x 10 x 1-inch. Bake 25 minutes.
Measure 1/4 cup pesto; set aside.
Spread remaining pesto evenly over chicken. Bake chicken 20 to 30 minutes longer or until chicken is no longer pink when cut into.
Mix pasta, tomatoes, zucchini and reserved pesto.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve pasta with chicken.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables or snack crackers.

title: finger jello
directions: Pour into broiler pan 2 1/2 cups cold water and gelatine.
Let set 5 minutes.
In saucepan put Jell-O, sugar and 2 cups hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Add to gelatine mixture and add 1 cup cold water.
Refrigerate and let set.
Cut in squares and put in plastic container.

title: cinnamon-almond sweet rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1 cup flour and salt in a large bowl; stir well.
Set aside.

title: morea's meat pie
directions: Saute diced onions in oil.
Add chopped meat to brown.
Take browned meat from skillet and drain in strainer.
Return drained meat to skillet and add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put meat into deep Pyrex pie plate.

title: english almond toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar, water and salt over low heat, stirring constantly until it boils.
Cook without stirring to 236° or until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Add almonds. Continue cooking to 290° (soft crack stage), stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Mixture turns to a deep caramel color.
Stir in soda.
Turn out onto greased baking sheet to 1/4-inch thickness. Immediately spread with chocolate pieces.
Spread chocolate as it melts; sprinkle with pecans.

title: breakfast omelet
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Add Tabasco to beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend into eggs.
Add meat, cheese and drained spinach.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 15 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand 1 hour.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cook until thick and set aside to cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour and mix in the oatmeal.
Line bottom and sides of pan with mixture.
Fill with the cut apples and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and dot with butter.
Cover the apples with the remaining mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken and sauce; cover with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef molded salad
directions: Dissolve cubes and jello in water and cool.
Add the Miracle Whip and cream cheese.
Beat with blender until smooth.
Fold in the rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: frosty date bars
directions: Cream butter
and confectioners sugar; stir in 1 tablespoon water and
teaspoon
vanilla.
Add
flour and dash of salt; mix well.
Stir
in
chopped dates and chopped walnuts. Roll in 1-inch
balls.
Place
2 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
in
a
slow oven (300°) for about 20 minutes, or until
cookies
are
set
and not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Stir and drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not mix.
Pour pie filling over mixture.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
May use blueberry, apple or peach pie mixture.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburg.
Cook bacon and onions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients except beans. Add beans and mix well.
Warm in crock-pot.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in salted water until done.
Drain and mash.
Mix crackers, egg, milk and part of the cheese into the squash.
Pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole.
Slice more of the cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and flour bottoms only of 2 baking pans (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 1 minute.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cool completely before slicing.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick cabbage casserole
directions: Slice cabbage or cut into chunks.
Cook in salted water until barely tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain well and place in casserole.
Mix soup, milk and cheese; pour over cabbage.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach in microwave and mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers, Hawaiian
bread or with cut vegetables.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together and put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cinnamon loaf
directions: Blend Crisco, 1 cup sugar, eggs, flour, milk, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Set aside.
Mix 3 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon together.
Put 1/3 batter in well-greased loaf pan, then 1/3 of sugar mixture.
Repeat until batter and sugar mixture are finished.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until well done. (Check center.)

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Each serving contains 140 calories = 1 1/2 bread and 1 fat.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Fill bottom of pan with broccoli.
Fry chicken (light brown). Lay chicken on top of broccoli (let frozen broccoli thaw a little). Mix soups with 1 cup of mayonnaise and 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
Then shred cheese and sprinkle some bread crumbs on top.
Dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve over white rice.

title: heath bar trifle
directions: Tear chocolate cake into pieces.
Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip, 3 of the crushed Heath bars, cake, liqueur, pudding, Cool Whip and remaining Heath bars (may have leftover cake). Refrigerate.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Bring dates and water to a boil, then allow to cool completely.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla, flour and pecans.
Mix as little as possible to combine.
Add cold boiled date mixture and mix lightly.
Bake in muffin tins at 425° 25-30 min. or until tops are dark.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add flavoring.
Add apples, walnuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Cook and crumble sausage; drain.
Roll thawed dough out to about 15 x 8-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese over dough, leaving about 1 inch border all around.
Top with sausage and spinach. Bring long sides of dough together; pinch to seal all edges.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet, seam side down, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.

title: twenty four hour salad
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and cream and cook in double boiler until thick and smooth.
Cool.
When cold, add lemon juice, then fold in whipping cream.
Add fruits, nuts and marshmallows. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
This is a delicious salad or dessert. Serves 14 to 18.

title: carrot sandwich
directions: Grind and drain carrots and you may prefer to grind nuts.
Mix all together and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: caramel crispy treats
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam (liberally); set aside. Place cereal in large bowl; set aside.
Unwrap caramels, place in 1-quart glass casserole.
Add marshmallows, margarine and water. Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Immediately stir melted mixture into cereal, tossing well to coat. Pour into pan and cool.
Makes 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand for 1 hour, stirring often.
Mix the flour, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and salt to the apple mixture, a little at a time.
Add to the combined mixture the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: the firebowl punch
directions: Heat wine but do not boil.
Add sliced fruit and cloves.
Add sugar to taste.

title: shrimp con queso
directions: Saute green onions, celery and green bell pepper in margarine. Add Ro-Tel (I use mild) and cream of celery soup. Add cheese and simmer, then add the cooked shrimp. Serve on white rice.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine together over medium heat, onion, tomato sauce, green chilies and Velveeta cheese until cheese is melted.
Brown ground beef; drain and add to mixture.
Fold in sour cream.
Soften tortillas in oil.
Layer mixture and tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Combine potato flakes, sour cream and 2/3 cup water.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; transfer to large bowl.

title: easy turkey tetrazzini
directions: In a
saucepan,
saute onion in margarine until tender. Blend in	soup,
water,
cheese and sherry.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir
now
and then. Add turkey, pimiento, parsley and vermicelli or spaghetti.
Heat.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skins with oil; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 to 1/8-inch shell.
(Pulp may be reserved for mashed potatoes or other uses.) Cut shells in half crosswise, and deep fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Place skins on a baking sheet; sprinkle with salt, cheese and bacon. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: chocolate goobers(candy)
directions: Combine sugar and crackers; set aside.
In saucepan, heat butter and peanut butter until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in crumb mixture.
Shape into walnut size balls and set aside.
In small saucepan, heat chocolate chips and shortening until melted. Roll balls in chocolate to coat.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased and floured stem cake pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: casey's banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding as directed except use TWO cups of milk, not three. Mix with Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Place layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of dish. Add layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding mix. Continue with layers until finished with bananas and pudding mix. Top with layer of vanilla wafers.

title: lumpia
directions: Fry ground beef until golden brown.
Mix in shrimp and onion. Add pepper, soy sauce, food Accent and salt to taste.
Mix.
Place 3 tablespoons mixture on each eggroll wrapper.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift powdered sugar into bowl.
Moisten with water and vanilla.
Drizzle over cake.
If glaze is too stiff, add a little more water.
Decorate top of cake with pecan halves.

title: just for kids edible play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
If mixture is sticky, add more confectioners sugar until at desired consistency.

title: mabel's casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Brown
the pork.
Put into large casserole along with the rest of the ingredients. Garnish with green pepper and cracker crumbs.
You may need another can of soup.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook
oysters in their own liquor until the edges curl. Add salt,
pepper
and	butter; slowly add milk.
Do not boil after milk is added, just heat slowly.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until barely tender. Drain well.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients to soup and sour cream mixture.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can fix in microwave oven.

title: quick fried chicken breasts
directions: Melt butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Salt and dip each piece of chicken breast in flour.
Brown well on both sides and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour lemon juice over fried pieces and sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Simmer another minute and serve.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine in a large baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white grape juice punch
directions: Mix.
Pour one of the plastic bottles 3/4 full.
Freeze until slushy.
Mix the slush with the other.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Place ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour on Spicy Herb Dressing and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine pudding, sugar, spice, milk, egg and pumpkin in pan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Remove.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring well.
Stir twice.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: shrewsbury cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and vanilla. Pour into tube pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots.
Add raisins, sugar and mayonnaise.
Toss until well blended.
For extra color and crispness, add diced apples or celery.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in pineapple chunks, cranberry sauce and chopped celery.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm. Serves 12.

title: chicken over pasta
directions: In large saucepan, empty soup and broth; add spices.
Cube up chicken and add to soup.
Simmer until chicken is tender (1/2 hour to 45 minutes).
Pour over noodles or gnocchi.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, over medium heat, melt 1 cup chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour evenly over crust, top with nuts and remaining chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: camper's cocoa
directions: Mix dry.
Add 1/2 cup of mix to cup; fill with hot water.

title: springtime fantasy
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip with an electric mixer until smooth.
Remove beaters.
Fold in crushed pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes.
(May add nuts or coconut, if desired.)

title: fudge sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat until well dissolved.

title: *spinach salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt, mustard, horseradish, vinegar and sour cream. Store in the refrigerator until ready to mix with spinach.
Vein one package of fresh spinach.
Break into bite size pieces.
Add small carton of cottage cheese to spinach.
Add pecans and dressing when ready to be served.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: bite-size cherry cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place on Nilla wafers in cupcake cups.
Bake in oven for 12 minutes.
When cool, place 2 to 3 cherries on top of each cheesecake.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine/butter with sugar.
Add eggs, mixing well. Add dry ingredients and flour.
Add sour cream.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Yields 30 (3-inch) cookies or 18 (5-inch) cookies.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Prepare your favorite pie crust in a 9 inch pan.
Peel peach halves and put them in unbaked pie shell, filling completely.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over peach halves.
Pour whipping cream over the sugar and flour mixture.
Dot with butter and bake at 375° until crust is brown and peaches are tender.

title: health food fudge
directions: In medium saucepan heat until smooth the honey, peanut butter and carob powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan and chill.

title: grill beef marinating sauce
directions: Mix together equal parts of fajita marinating sauce, garlic sauce and Italian dressing.
Add a "little" mustard and salt and pepper to taste.

title: macaroni-dried beef casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Can be baked in a.m. and reheated.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth and boil syrup.
Drop peaches in boiling syrup.
Cook soft and then seal at once.

title: icebox cake
directions: Roll wafers and line dish with half of crumbs.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Cover wafers with filling.
Then add a layer of drained pineapple.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cherry salad
directions: In a saucepan bring to a boil the cherries and the sugar. Take from stove and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Can add 1/2 cup of nuts.

title: caraway seed dip
directions: Beat cheese until soft; add enough sour cream to make dip consistency.
Add caraway seed.
Can add 1 tablespoon Hellmann's mayonnaise.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in pineapple, then milk.
Fold in bread cubes.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart dish at 325° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: good lasagna
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet with onions (salt and pepper the meat as it cooks).
Drain off the fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through (10 to 15 minutes).

title: jeanette's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a mixing bowl until well mixed.
Blend together sugar and flour and add slowly to eggs while still beating.
Add corn, one can at a time, and mix well.
Cut margarine into 1/4-inch pieces and fold into
mixture.
Pour into a deep, 2-quart baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir gently twice during baking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients with an electric mixer. Add the 2 cheeses. Mix until well blended. Place mixture in the freezer for 30 minutes. Remove from freezer and shape into ball. Roll cheese ball in finely ground walnuts. Place on plate and cover with plastic wrap until ready to use.

title: yam casserole
directions: Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until topping is slightly brown.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Put pork and beans in casserole.
Stir in sugar and mustard. Stir in part of bacon.
Put the rest of the bacon and the catsup on top.
Stir well.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl at once.
Beat at medium speed for 12 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Don't open oven door.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: nibbles mix
directions: Put oyster crackers in a paper bag.
Add garlic powder, lemon pepper, dill weed and ranch dressing.
Pour oil over all above. Shake well.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat well and pour into the crust.
Chill and serve.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Stir macaroni in 6 cups boiling water.
Boil 7 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Drain.
Add margarine or butter, 1/4 cup of 2% milk and contents of sauce packet.
Mix well.

title: lo-cal italian chicken skillet
directions: In large nonstick frypan, over high heat, place chicken and cook, turning, until brown on all sides.
Push chicken to one side of pan.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Stir and cook 5 minutes.
In bowl, place whole tomatoes; stir in garlic salt, parsley flakes, oregano, basil, pepper and vinegar.
Add to frypan.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove cover and cook 10 minutes more or until fork-tender.

title: sauteed potato cubes
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil the potatoes and enough salted water to cover.
Reduce heat; simmer for about 2 minutes.
Drain. In skillet, heat oil.
Add potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook, shaking skillet occasionally and stirring gently, about 10 minutes or until potatoes are nicely browned.
Drain in colander. Return to skillet; add butter.
Over high heat, toss potatoes about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup boiling water. Add 1/4 cup cold water. Add cream cheese and mayonnaise. Mix with beater. Add chopped vegetables to gelatin mixture, then salt, pepper and
dill weed to taste. Pour into serving container and refrigerate until set. Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: squash relish
directions: Chop the squash, onions and peppers and mix well with the salt; let stand for 1 hour.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour it over squash, onions and peppers and boil 5 to 10 minutes, then can.

title: hungarian salad
directions: Cut potatoes, tomatoes and green peppers into thin slices and arrange in a bowl.
Combine vinegar, oil, salt, black pepper and paprika.
Mix together and use as dressing.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drain potatoes and rice while hot.
Mix cream, egg yolks, salt, onion juice, cheese and parsley.
Add to riced potatoes and whip until fluffy. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into potato mixture.
Pile lightly into 8 mounds on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Mix well, pour into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for an hour or more.

title: frosty hermits
directions: Measure Kellogg's

All Bran into small bowl. Add milk, let stand until moisture is taken up. Sift flour, soda and spices, set aside. Beat sugar and butter or margarine, until light and fluffy. Add eggs, vanilla and All-Bran mixture, beat well. Add
sifted ingredients, stir until mixed. Stir in Planters Peanuts and raisins. Drop by level tablespoonful onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven 375°
about 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from baking sheet. If desired frost with vanilla icing and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Cream, butter, sugar and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.
Beat again until well blended and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk. Stir gently only until moist.
Fold in banana and nuts.
Transfer to greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: mocha fudge pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 22 minutes.

title: mamie turner's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time; sift flour 3 times.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream, baking soda, bourbon and vanilla.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Put cake into cold oven and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: party punch
directions: In a gallon pitcher add:
sugar, Kool aid, 3 cups hot water. Stir until sugar is melted.
Add juice, stir.
Add ice until container is almost full.
(Leave room for a can or two of soda to be added at the last minute.)

title: squash pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add a time.
Stir in other ingredients.
Use unbaked pie crust.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Pulse until thoroughly blended.
Use as dressing for fresh fruit salad for a special tropical taste.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble. Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings. Saute onion and celery in drippings until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Stir in bacon and potatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil chicken until tender. Shred or cube. In large bowl, combine chicken pieces, water chestnuts, onion, soup and most of the cereal crumbs. Pour mixture into 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle remaining flakes on top of mixture. Bake for 1 hour.

title: fried rice sticks with pork
directions: Partially freeze pork; thinly slice pork and then cut into shreds.
Pour enough boiling water over rice sticks to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain well.

title: butterscotch taffy
directions: Boil all together until ball forms in cold water.
Pour in buttered pan, cool and crack into pieces.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled, at least 2 hours.
Drop onto aluminum ungreased cookie sheet with ice cream scoop.
Bake 22 to 24 minutes at 300°.

title: bean casserole supreme
directions: Put all beans in a large casserole.
Mix and set aside.
Saute chopped onions in oil.
Add the brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and garlic powder to the onions; simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over top of beans.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle bacon or Bac*Os on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 10 servings.

title: corn puffs
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook to 280°.
Pour over 3 packages of corn puffs.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer until tender (1 hour).
Drain pineapple (save syrup), combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork; cook and stir until gravy thickens. Add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: chicken florentine
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat melt 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add chicken and cook until browned on all sides.
Add water, pepper and bouillon.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix with hand.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: la louisianne potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain and turn into large mixing bowl.
Mash and beat (with electric mixer) potatoes, sour cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper and butter.
Pour into butter-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir soup until smooth and spread over top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: summer squash mexican style
directions: Cut corn from cob; discard cobs.
In pot, combine butter and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add squash, corn, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover, cook slowly, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.
Can be topped with strawberries or blueberries or any other topping, if desired.

title: raisinette oatmeal cookies
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Cream Crisco and liquid ingredients.
Mix dry and creamed ingredients together.
Add nuts and Raisinettes. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: char's casserole
directions: Brown the onion, green pepper and celery with the beef.
Put into casserole dish and then add soy sauce, soup and milk to mixture.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well. Stir in flavoring.
(Dough will be stiff.) Chill dough at least 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Place a marshmallow half on top of each. Bake 2 more minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Over low heat place 2 c. water into saucepan and mix jello marshmallows and cream cheese. Heat until dissolved. Put aside until it begins to set.
Fold cool whip into mixture along with drained pineapple. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate.

title: "my man" cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Then add rest of ingredients.
Add buttermilk, if it is too dry.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water
for
10 minutes. Empty drained tuna into large 2-quart baking
dish.
Add	all the ingredients and cooked, drained
macaroni;	mixing	well. Saute the crushed chips or crackers in melting margarine; then sprinkle on	top of casserole.
Bake at 375°
for
to
25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients into punch bowl.
Stir together and serve.
Add slices of limes for decoration.
Serve chilled.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Cream in powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Whip in Cool Whip.
Put in cool baked pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: "prize winning" dirt cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with pudding; fold in cool whip.
In flower pot, layer: cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding, etc...until all is used, ending with cookies. Stick a few gummy worms in cookie "dirt" and chill; serve with cool whip.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Mix together the flour, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup margarine. Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs, sugar, 1 1/2 cups flour, rhubarb and salt and spread over crust. Mix brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour, 1/4 cup margarine and cinnamon and sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mandarin delight
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in 1 cup of boiling water. Add 1 cup reserved pineapple and mandarin orange juice.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges to jello.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top mixture with miniature marshmallows. Chill until firm.
Just before serving, combine mayonnaise and sour cream and spread like a frosting on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
A very pretty salad.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Have a parent preheat oven to 450°.
Roll biscuit 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2 oblong pieces (plastic knife).
Roll each piece around a hot dog cut whatever length you like, letting tip show on ends.
Seal by pinching edge of dough.
Bake with sealed edge underneath, about 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 12.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In bottom of 8-inch square serving dish, mix refried beans with 1/2 package taco seasoning and onions as desired.
Spread evenly.

title: stuffed green pepper
directions: Clean and boil peppers until tender.
Follow pkg.
directions to make rice.
Brown and drain hamburger.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Then add chocolate chips. Serve on graham crackers.

title: peas and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened milk, ReaLemon and rind.
Turn into pie shell.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy; gradually adding sugar and beating until stiff but not dry.
Spread on top of pie and bake 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.
Cool before serving.

title: bev's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and onion together according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm and top is lightly browned.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Arrange sauerkraut on bottom of baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour V-8 juice over top.
Place pork chops on top of mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, make several layers of vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour the cooled filling over this.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into 3 loaves.
Put in large baking pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and poke holes in top of loaves.
Pour sauce over tops.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour or until done.
Baste loaves at times while they bake.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine and blend well milk and lemon juice.
Add the rest of the ingredients until well mixed. Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate a couple of hours before serving.
Garnish top with mandarin oranges or however you wish.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on the rack of an unheated broiler pan; season chops with salt and pepper.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn chops.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes more or until done.
Brush chops liberally with taco sauce; place chili pepper strips atop chops.
Top evenly with shredded cheese.
Broil just until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt all ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat.
Season with Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven or deep kettle.
Add water, onion, parsley, salt and whole black peppercorns.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool and remove meat from bones. Dice meat.
Strain broth and return to kettle.
Bring stock to boiling and add noodles, celery, shredded carrots, salt, thyme and oregano.
Return to boil.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Add chicken and heat.
Makes 2 1/2-quarts.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Press dough into greased 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch pan. Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Spread batter over dough.
Top with chips and pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 - 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: bridal shower punch
directions: Chill all liquid ingredients. Pour all over ice mold, adding Cold Duck last. It is a light alcoholic punch for a ladies special function.

title: icy cranberry slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium-sized bowl.
Freeze in airtight containers.

title: lo-cal fresh strawberry sauce
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar in a small bowl.
Let stand until syrup forms (about 1 hour).
Drain syrup into a 1-cup glass measure, reserving strawberries.
Add water to strawberry syrup to make 1/2 cup.

title: mexican pick-ups
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Heat tortillas per directions. Spread some cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas and then refrigerate for several hours.
Cut each roll into 5 bite-sized pieces.
Secure each piece with a toothpick.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: honey and garlic chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a bowl combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place chicken in a 4 qt. slow cooker and pour sauce over. Cook on low for 6-8 hours.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: mexican stack-up for twenty
directions: Use pie dough, enough for a two crust pie, your favorite recipe or prepared crust.
Cut each round crust in two pieces.

title: beef-greens-potato green beans
directions: Saute onion in vegetable oil 2 to 3 minutes.
Crumble ground beef or turkey and cook.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Blend soup with liquid; add to skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Cook potatoes and green beans until done.
Add to skillet and simmer gently until flavors are blended; do not boil.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into melted oleo.
Pour peaches and juice into this.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Put nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by box directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and margarine together.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Drizzle over cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes or until done.
Stick may be moist from cream cheese. Turn upside-down on cookie sheet and leave 5 minutes and take off.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Grease oblong baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 inches.
Layer chicken and broccoli in dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices on soup mixture.
Mix baking mix and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with tomato slices, if desired. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and spices, sifted together.
If nuts are used, add to mixture after flouring.
Knead well on floured board. Divide into several portions.
Roll and chill.
Slice thinly.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.
You may freeze these rolls of cookie dough and cook as you wish at later dates.

title: busy day pot roast
directions: Place roast in a large, heavy pan (an iron skillet with lid is ideal); spread mushroom soup over the meat and sprinkle mix over the top.
(Do not use salt.)
Surround meat with whole, peeled potatoes and carrots, if you wish, to complete your meal.
Cover pan and bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Needs no watching!

title: strawberry jam bars
directions: Grease and sugar 9-inch square pan. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and cook cake as directed in a 13 x 9 pan.
Let cool. Punch holes all in cake with a straw or wooden spoon.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin slices.
Coat with milk and then flour. Melt butter in a large frypan.
Brown all chicken well.
When all the chicken is browned, remove.
Add sliced lemon and garlic until garlic is brown and lemon is soft.
Add chicken broth and chicken. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, 1 1/2 cups of the milk, sugar and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and creamy, 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend remaining 1/2 cup of milk and egg.
Stir into rice mixture.
Add raisins.
Cook 2 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and vanilla. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.

title: chocolate ooey-gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and egg. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage with a knife.
Layer with sliced onions and sprinkle on 3/4 cup sugar.

title: *vegetable casserole
directions: Saute almonds with bacon in 10 to 12-inch skillet.
When almonds are lightly roasted and bacon is crisp, remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Add zucchini, eggplant and onion to skillet.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until tender, about 30 minutes, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Mix in flour, then add tomatoes.
Stir in garlic, salt, pepper and basil.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until firm.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Shred Velveeta and mix through broccoli.
Put in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Crush 1 stick Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Put cracker mixture on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Beat oleo.
Add brown sugar and beat well.
Beat in eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers, vegetables and/or bread cubes.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the dates.
Mix butter with sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the date-water and sugar mix.
Add the walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: In large kettle over medium heat mix cranberry juice, water, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Drain off spices if you like.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: christmas cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours.
Line angel food pan with brown paper.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, add soda, salt, half of sifted flour with lemon extract; beat until smooth.
Finish adding flour, mixing well. Take 1/2 cup flour and mix with raisins.
Fold pecans and raisins into mixture, then fold egg whites into mixture.
Pour into lined pan and bake.
This is a family tradition at our house.

title: mom's chocolate layer cake
directions: In one bowl, mix flour, sugar and salt.
In another bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
In a saucepan, mix water, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Mix together dry ingredients, egg mixture and hot mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased and floured) and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish. Top with paprika and more grated cheese if desired. Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 45 minutes.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco gradually.
Add milk, then add eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, layer 1/2 rice, sour cream, peppers and cheese.
Layer again with rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger; cool.
Drain pineapple and spread on cake.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese; spread on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix together.
On top spread 1 cup bread crumbs (fine) and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Cook in greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be served over pastry shells.

title: chicken in tomato basil cream
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute onion in butter in medium skillet for 5 minutes.
Turn heat to high.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Cook until reduced (4 minutes).
Add cream.
Bring to boil; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in basil, salt and pepper.
Place chicken breasts into shallow baking pan.
Pour cream sauce over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sauced mostaccioli
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; remove and reserve.
In same skillet, cook onion and garlic until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste and salt.
Add reserved beef, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: frozen chocolate almond pie(microwave)
directions: Special Note:
This pie cuts well straight from the freezer. No thawing is necessary.
Use a wet knife for sharpest cut.

title: frosted graham loaf
directions: Beat cream, cocoa, salt and sugar until very thick and spreadable.
Spread about 1/4 on each graham cracker, standing each up on the long edge in front of the last one frosted, to form a continuous straight row.
Frost all sides and tops.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat.
Pour over combined remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt evelyn's barbecue sauce(wonderful for grilling chicken outdoors.)
directions: Cook onion in oil. Add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: brownie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare an 8-inch square pan with vegetable pan coating.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over medium heat; cool.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add oat bran cereal, flour and 1/4 cup nuts.
Mix just until well blended.
Spread into prepared pan; sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake about 18 minutes or until firm to the touch. Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Use 1 cup salt to a gallon of pickles.
Add water to cover; let stand for 7 days.
On 8th day, drain off salt water and cover with boiling water.
On the 9th day, drain off water and split pickles.
Cover with alum and boiling water.
On the 10th day, drain off alum water and cover with boiling water.
On the 11th day, drain again and add 1/4 quart vinegar (fill the quart with water), white sugar, celery seed, allspice and cinnamon sticks (broken).
Cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: sherry beef
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Place in casserole dish with rest of ingredients and cook, covered, for 3 hours at 350°.
Serves 8. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: jelly roll
directions: Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil, then grease with shortening.
Beat eggs in a large bowl on high speed until thick and lemon color.
Gradually beat in sugar. Beat in water and vanilla on low speed.
Gradually beat in flour, baking powder and salt until smooth.
Pour into pan; spread to corners.
Bake at 375°.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 12 to 15 minutes.
Generously sprinkle powdered sugar on a towel a little larger than the cake.

title: apple coffeecake
directions: Blend the sugar and cinnamon.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with 1 tablespoon of cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Blend cake mix with applesauce and eggs.
Beat well.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter and pour remaining in pan.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over batter in pan, then pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: old-time bread pudding
directions: Place toast into greased 1 1/4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Combine eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Pour over toast.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut well and squeeze dry.
May be rinsed in cold water first.
Add diced ingredients and mix.
