Add sugar and mix. Combine vinegar and oil; pour into other ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 6 to 8 weeks.

title: jello cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together, then stir in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls and flatten with a glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans (8 or 9-inch oblong or 13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Measure dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add soup and shortening; beat at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add eggs and water and beat for 2 minutes.

title: apple grape punch
directions: In 1 gallon jar combine juices and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Serve over ice. Garnish with apple slices and grapes, if desired.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1 pint screw-top jar and shake until blended.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: easy cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix together all ingredients and press into the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken in covered water.
Remove meat from bones and cut up.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, milk, onions and salt.
Put 5 to 6 tablespoons of broth in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chips, chicken and half of soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours and then bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cover with cheese and melt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until
tender.
Add
onion and simmer for a few minutes
longer.
Add
remaining ingredients and pour into an ovenproof baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: oyster fritter
directions: Make a batter of the eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt and pepper.
Stir the oysters into the batter and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil or grease.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar and butter. Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and water.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Pour into containers and freeze until ready to serve.
Thaw slightly and add 2 quarts ginger ale.

title: old-time remedy for cold
directions: Squeeze juice of 2 lemons in a glass of hot water, sweetened; add soda, sufficient to cause fermentation.
Drink immediately after stirring in the soda and take it before retiring.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Prepare
care
as
directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from pan and place in freezer for 1 hour. Remove from
freezer
and
split
in half lengthwise, using a large knife or dental floss.
Mix well the 5 tablespoons flour and
milk. Cook
until
thick;
set aside and cool.
Then mix well
the sugar, margarine, Crisco, salt and vanilla and beat at high speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread between cake layers.
You may top cake with Cool Whip if desired.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a big bowl or pan; keep warm. Stir in enough flour to make an extremely thick dough.
Cover.
Set in warm place away from drafts for 2 to 3 hours.
When dough has doubled in size, stir it down, pour out on floured board with lots of flour.
Knead in flour until dough appears dry.
Place in large greased pan and cover.
Let set until doubled again.
Knead down in pan.
Pour onto floured board and knead in flour until dough won't take any more.
Pinch off in pieces and put in greased pans.
Bake slowly in 300° oven until well browned.
Brush melted oleo over tops.
Serve hot.
Keeps well and can be frozen for later use.

title: toss salad
directions: Core lettuce and tear into chunks.
Combine all ingredients, except the croutons, in a large bowl and toss well.
Add croutons just before serving.

title: lazy man chicken pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Put chicken in baking dish. Pour soup mixed with broth on top of chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine on top of soup.
Bake at 350°.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes to make one cup.
(Do not use milk.)
Mix well the potatoes, hot water, butter, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and dissolved yeast.
Stir in flour until dough resembles very heavy muffin batter.
Cover. Let rise in warm water until doubled.
Punch down (I let mine rise twice).
Spread in five 9-inch greased layer cake pans (or ungreased foil pans).
Cover; let rise to top of pans.
Punch holes in batter.
Sprinkle top of batter with cinnamon, fill holes with butter.
Cover tops of pans with brown sugar (with a small amount of flour).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Sugar cake freezes well.
To serve, thaw and warm gently.

title: ollie's apple cake
directions: In mixing bowl, break eggs over grated apples.
Mix with a fork.
Do not beat!
Into this mixture, add sugar, salt, oil, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix again with fork.
Add flour (with each cup, add 1 teaspoon baking soda).
Again, do not beat!!!!
Add nuts.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in Bundt pan at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Great served in pita pockets.

title: season salt mixture
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. Makes about 1 cup.
Use to season oil and vinegar dressing, meat, fish and vegetables.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 1/2 hour.
Beat sugar and egg yolks together until light in color.
Add to crumb mixture and mix well.
Stir in lemon juice and grated rind and butter. Pour
into greased
pudding
dish and bake until light brown. Whip
egg whites
until
frothy;
add
4 tablespoons powdered sugar
and beat
until very stiff.
When pudding is done, top with
jelly, then egg whites.
Return to oven and brown. Serve warm.

title: funny cake
directions: Pour on top of cake batter in the pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cover; bring to boil.
Remove cover.
Cook to 242° on candy thermometer.
Just before syrup is ready, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup over egg whites very slowly while beating with electric mixer.
Beat until frosting holds peaks.
Blend in vanilla.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers and onions.
Mix.
Add sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour boiled mixture over cabbage mixture.
Seal in airtight container.
Do not stir or uncover for 4 hours.

title: helga's coconut crispies
directions: Mix sugar and butter. Add eggs. Add coconut and oatmeal.
Add vanilla.
Mix soda and baking powder into flour. Add flour to above mixture.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Pat out with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Have Cool Whip at room temperature.
Melt candy bar and fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into shell and refrigerate.
Easy and delicious!

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt the butter, brown sugar, and cinnamon in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Layer 2 layers of bread in pan on top of sugar mixture. Mix 5 beaten eggs, the vanilla, and milk. Pour over bread and let sit in refrigerator overnight. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve upside down.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken into bite sized pieces and place in casserole dish.
Dilute soups with milk and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and the chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and chips.
Put into a casserole and bake 20 or 25 minutes at 350°.

title: grape pie
directions: Wash and drain grapes.
Remove skins, but do not discard. Place grape pulp in a saucepan; bring slowly to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes and force through a sieve to remove seeds.
Combine sieved pulp and skins.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and salt; add to pulp.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cinnamon and butter; cool.
Turn into baked shell.

title: chicken with mayo and parmesan cheese
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese together.
Spread mixture over chicken fillets and coat with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until tender.

title: boston fudge cake
directions: Sift the flour with soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla and beat for 2 minutes, scraping bowl constantly.
Add unbeaten eggs and melted chocolate. Continue beating for 2 more minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool layers and put together with Brown Butter Icing.

title: portia's banana wheat bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir well.
Combine banana, oil, honey, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Spoon into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until it tests done.
Makes 1 loaf (9 x 5 x 3-inch).

title: chip dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in microwave.
Add chili and peppers and mix well.
Cook 3 minutes on medium setting.
Add Cheddar on top and serve with corn chips.

title: tasty cake
directions: Boil 1 cup of milk and then add 2 teaspoons butter (do not scorch milk).
Set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguini and drain.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate several hours.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Chop all in food processor except shrimp.
Add shrimp after all is mixed well.
Process just long enough for shrimp to mix in. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: romaine lettuce and chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients before serving.

title: black bean soup
directions: Brown sliced turkey sausage in nonstick pan.
Put browned sausage in large pot with all other ingredients.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Thirty minutes before soup is done, take out 1/4 to 1/3 of beans.
Put in blender and make a paste, then put back into soup to thicken.
Garnish with fat-free cheese or fat-free sour cream.

title: aunt goldie's biscotti
directions: Whip together first 5 ingredients.
Combine next 4 ingredients and stir into first mixture.
When well blended, divide into three loaves and arrange on a greased cookie sheet (lengthwise).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan. Bring to a rapid boil; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir with a fork until smooth.
Using a large spoon, drop on a cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put the first 2 ingredients in the blender to be chopped. Then add the other ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl dissolve jello in hot water, then mix with other ingredients.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To make one cup hot tea, use 2 1/2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix pudding, lemonade and milk together.
Mix until smooth. Fold 3/4 of cool whip into mixture.
Pour into crust and top with remaining cool whip. 8 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn & milk. Stir in egg. Add 3/4 c. crumbs, pimento, onion, salt & pepper. Pour into oiled casserole dish. Melt butter in small skillet. Brown remainder of crumbs. Spread on top of corn mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: jamaican shrimp and rice
directions: Dice the bacon and fry pieces until they are translucent but not dry.
Add the oil, onion and raw shrimp. Stir well until shrimp are pink. Stir well to make sure that all ingredients are well coated with oil.
Add the rice, then pour in the water.
Stir again. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat.
It should be ready in about 30 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat Cokes and dissolve Jell-O in the Cokes.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add cheese, pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: best corn bread
directions: Melt
margarine
in
medium
size cast-iron frying pan. Pour margarine into dry ingredients with milk.
Stir and pour into pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pimiento cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix cheese and the 2 jars of pimiento together using enough mayonnaise to make spreading consistency. Add Tabasco
sauce to taste.
Spread on bread and cut as desired.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken breasts, bread crumbs and butter.
Place the chicken in a large bowl; pour liquid over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: yummy quick chess cake
directions: First: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Pat into 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, onions, garlic, salt, pepper and celery.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and green pepper.
Roll in balls.

title: meat loaf in the round
directions: Combine ground beef, 1 cup cheese, bread crumbs, egg, celery, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Place in a shallow 9-inch round pan and flatten ball almost to sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off drippings and pour tomato sauce over meat.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of remaining shredded cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes. Cut into pie-shaped wedges to serve.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine or butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and salt; cook 2 minutes over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Add milk. Stir constantly until milk comes to boil.
Remove from stove.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar gradually, add vanilla flavoring. If too thick, additional milk may be added.
Spread on cake (one layer or one layer cut in half).

title: easy sesame candies
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In 1-quart saucepan stir together the corn syrup, sugar and margarine.
Stirring occasionally, bring to full rolling boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in sesame seed.
Spread evenly in pan.
Cool. Remove from pan, break into pieces.
Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add carrots, brown sugar, dry mustard and salt. Cover and cook about 20 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in large casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix fruit juices; add ginger ale and ice cubes just before serving.
Fruit juices may be frozen and used with the ginger ale while still in the "slush" stage.

title: bacalhau albardado (fried codfish)
directions: Remove skin and bones from the cooked codfish.
Break into large chunks, drying with a towel.
Make a batter with flour, oil and water.
Add egg yolks, parsley and egg whites beaten until stiff; salt and pepper to taste.
Dip codfish chunks into batter and fry in oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: stuff
directions: Put into a
buttered
casserole all ingredients, except the cheese, in the order given.
Bake
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Spread cheese on top for the last 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and knead a few minutes.
Put into buttered bowl and let rise for 1 hour.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and slice.
Put into buttered tins and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Add pineapple and put in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on box, then add the Dream Whip, cottage cheese and nuts to Jell-O.
Return to refrigerator.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll into ball and then roll in chopped pecans.

title: cheesy macaroni and spam casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Mix mushroom soup, Spam and pimentos together.
Make layer of mixture; spread layer of cheese.
Repeat layer of mixture and top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix orange juice, pudding and milk with beater for 2 minutes on low speed.
Add sour cream and beat for a couple of seconds until smooth.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple chunks, apple slices, orange slices and banana slices.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook pasta.
Brown meat; stir in sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and seasonings.
Toss pasta with meat sauce.

title: pork roast with minted couscous
directions: Ask butcher to "crack" the pork loin roast as that the roast is cut through at the bone.
Coat with salt and pepper.
Put fresh or dried rosemary between each "crack." Coat outside with rosemary.
Bake at 350° after first broiling for a few minutes to brown the roast.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours until done.
Serve with cooked couscous which has been flavored with 1/4 cup olive oil and chopped, fresh mint.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar; stir until dissolved.
Mix all ingredients.
Ladle into Dixie cups and freeze.
Recipe compliments a brunch nicely or make a refreshing summer treat. Thaw about 1 hour before serving.

title: hash brown and egg brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In deep 9-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and peppers; cook until onion is softened. Add potatoes and cook, covered, over medium heat 5 minutes.
Beat eggs and cream together; stir in chiles, salt and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Cover and bake 10 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 15 to 17 minutes until set in center.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and onion.
Add beans (undrained). Mix together remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together good; pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients in small bowl while browning ground beef.
Mix with ground beef and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Crumble brownies after they cool, into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding mixes with 3 cups milk and sour cream.
Pour over brownies.
Crumble Heath bars with a hammer.
(I use a plastic bag and hammer for crumbling.)
Put over pudding and brownies.
Last, add Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: quick baked chicken breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 8 ingredients. Brush on chicken breasts, coating completely. Place breasts in buttered 13x9x2 inch baking dish. Bake for 1 hour.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Add margarine and vanilla. Pour in shell.
Top with meringue made from egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all filling ingredients together; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: fat-free cherry pie
directions: Spray glass baking dish with Pam.
Spread 1/2 of the cherry pie filling.
Mix flour and milk to thicken (not too thin). Pour or spoon 1/2 over cherry filling.
Add the rest of the filling (gently), then add rest of flour mix.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown.

title: mocha cream torte
directions: Dissolve coffee in water in double boiler. Add marshmallows. Stir until smooth. Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix until well blended. Fold in whipped topping. Fill and frost cake.
Chill well before serving.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Melt butter and add flour and salt.
Add milk to flour mixture.
Cook until thick.
Reduce heat. Add cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Pour sauce over vegetables and mix slightly.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet about 20 minutes.
Serve balls with toothpicks.
Makes about 30.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish.
Pour in hot water.
Cream butter.
Add flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frosty freeze pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended. Add sherbet; mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Pour into crust; freeze until firm.

title: rolls
directions: Put the macaroni in the pot.
Then pour the cheese in.
Bake it for 15 minutes.

title: ms. rachel's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and boil about 15 minutes.
Ready to spread on chicken.
This makes enough for 12 whole chickens.
Freeze any extra.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: virginia cotton's delicious, easy and cheap barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and heat.
Pour over chicken and place in a covered dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese; add milk gradually, then add cherries and fruit.
Place in mold or container and freeze at least 4 hours before serving.

title: thai shrimp and sesame noodles
directions: In a medium bowl, mix shrimp with 1/3 cup salad dressing. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or less.

title: easy chili pie
directions: Crush 2 cups Fritos and spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and half of cheese on crushed corn chips.
Spread chili over chips, cheese and onion.
Top with remaining cheese and corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pig licking good cake
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Mix well.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350°. Cool.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits per instructions on grits box.
Add butter and Cheez Whiz; stir until melted.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add both to grits.
Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
(If you wish to use the garlic, add it to the Cheez Whiz.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: glenna's chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread on marshmallow cream and icing.

title: caramel apple oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in margarine or butter until crumbly, reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remaining on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add nuts to reserved crumb mixture.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar into skillet.
Chop artichokes (both jars drained) and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in marinade 5 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and hot pepper seasoning sauce.
Stir in cheese.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cut in squares.
(May be frozen after baking.
After thawing, serve cold or reheat about 10 minutes.)

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 20 minutes. Then cut into one inch chunks. Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and ginger. Add orange juice. Cook, stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles. Boil one minute. Stir in butter. Pour over hot carrots, toss to coat evenly.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring to a boil for approximately 1 minute.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour in pan. Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on batter.
With knife, cut through batter several times for marbled effect. Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy streusel pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
In large bowl, whisk together eggs, pumpkin, milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of spice.
Pour filling into one frozen crust.
Bake on baking sheet 30 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and shred coarsely.
Heat butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring until partially melted.
Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Place in greased 2-quart dish, dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: red raspberry jam
directions: Boil sugar and water together until syrup threads.
Wash and drain berries; crush and measure.
Add to syrup; cook rapidly while stirring for 20 minutes, when mixture should have thickened. Place in hot jars and cool.
Seal with paraffin.
Fills 6 (6 ounce) glasses.

title: fruit ball
directions: Lay out cream cheese to soften.
Drain and squeeze juice from pineapple and discard.
Soften cream cheese in mixer with powdered sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well with spoon or hands. Shape into ball and chill.
Add additional nuts to cover ball before or after chilling.
Serve with Town House or Ritz crackers.

title: old fashion tea cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out on floured surface about 1/4-inch thick. Cut into desired shape.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Will also need muffin papers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla and butter for 10 minutes. This step is very important.
Add eggs and continue to beat. Spread over crumbs.
Peel bananas and cut in lengthwise halves. Place over cream layer.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt oil and butter in pan. Combine flour and seasoning. Shake in a bag. Place in pan, skin down. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Turn 5 to 10 minutes (crust bubbly).

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix in the pan it is to be cooked in.
Mix ingredients in order and stir with a fork.
Bake at 375° until cake springs back at touch.
Cool and frost.

title: baked corn
directions: Chop and saute in butter the onion, bell pepper and celery. Mix and add rest of ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 19-inch or two smaller pans for 1 hour at 350°.
When using two, I freeze one.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Blend.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: cafe brulot
directions: Place sugar, orange rind and vanilla pod in heatproof bowl; bruise rind with wooden spoon.
Pour brandy into small saucepan; place over low heat until heated through.
Pour over sugar mixture.
Ignite; stir constantly 30 seconds.
Extinguish flames with hot coffee.
Remove orange rind and vanilla pod.
Serve in coffee cups.
Do not serve with cream or additional sugar.
Yield: about 20 demitasse cups.

title: long island ice tea
directions: Mix in tall glass 5 shots of rum, vodka, gin, tequila and Triple Sec.
Add 1 cup Coke and jigger of bar sours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Add noodles, soup and sauce.
Mix together and pour into 7 x 11-inch greased dish. Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top and cover for 10 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease tube pan; tear one loaf of thawed bread in bite size pieces and arrange on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of pudding mix and cinnamon.
Tear up other loaf of bread and arrange pieces the same way.
Sprinkle other half of pudding mix and cinnamon. Heat butter and brown sugar until boiling.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool 6 minutes.
Remove to plate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine and drop in 4x sugar.
Put on cookie sheet and press down; put jam or jelly in center.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Flatten dough to fit pan, sealing seams and perforations.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown; cool.
In a small bowl, blend cream cheese and sour cream; spread over crust.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Spread pieces with raspberry jam. Cook pudding with 1 teaspoon of vanilla according to package directions.
Layer into bowl as follows:
cake, pudding, fruit and whipped cream.
May top with sliced almonds and fresh fruit as sliced strawberries or cherries as garnish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Add the 1/2 cup sugar to the peaches and boil.
Drain peaches. Add 1 1/4 cups sugar to peach juice and boil.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk.
Stir enough to mix.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Spread peaches on dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice into 1-inch pieces and lay in buttered dish.
Pour sugar and juice over slices.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: grandma bonvino's cookies(biscotto di nonna)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and extract.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Stir
in
chocolate chips.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly golden. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits, in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (cover with foil).
Remove covering; place biscuits on top of mixture.
Return to oven; bake, uncovered, 12 minutes longer.
Serves 5.

title: herbed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots.
Cut into quarters (lengthwise), then halves (lengthwise).
Cook in hot water and salt, covered.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add herbs and butter.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into slightly oiled oblong glass dish.
Chill until congealed.

title: dee's layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top
with
crumbled
bacon, 3 to 4 sliced boiled eggs, 3 sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber and tomato skillet
directions: Slice cucumbers into 1-inch slices.
Slice onion into rings. Slice tomatoes into wedges.
Heat margarine in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Cook cucumbers and onions about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp.
Stir in tomatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, just until tomatoes are hot.
Sprinkle with dill.
Serves 6.

title: candied holiday cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wrap in wax paper in rolls; freeze. Slice thin and bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not let brown.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in large container.
Use 1/3 cup of cocoa mix in a mug.
Fill rest of mug with hot water. Stir.
You may float a marshmallow on top or Cool Whip.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soak onion soup in hot water for 1/2 hour.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Blend mixture into cream cheese and beat to make smooth paste.
Add milk.
Beat well again.
Serve with vegetable nibblers or crackers.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks. Add salt. Stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon (almost to a boil). Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar and beat into soft peaks.
Add to custard and mix thoroughly. Add flavorings and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Pour into punch bowl.
Dot with "islands" of whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings. Enjoy!

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Roll bread slices flat with a rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread a scant tablespoon on each slice; roll up slightly.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon in a shallow bowl.
Brush roll-ups (including ends) with butter; roll in sugar mixture to coat.
Place on cookie sheet; refrigerate or freeze at least 2 hours.
(To store, freeze up to 2 months.)
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake roll-ups on cookie sheet 9 to 12 minutes until bottoms are glazed and golden brown.
Remove immediately to a wire rack to cool.
Cut each diagonally in 3 pieces.
Eat warm or cold. Yield: 72 pieces.

title: bran muffins(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given; let stand one hour and mix again.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Bake in greased cupcake tins at 375° for 25 minutes or microwave in microwavable muffin tin 5 minutes on High (depending on your microwave power.)

title: grandma's pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine pumpkin, Sugar Twin, salt and spices. Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (crimp edges high, filling is generous.)
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Use 10-inch pie shell if desired.

title: daffodil cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in 3/4 cup of sugar; add 1 teaspoon vanilla; add 1/2 cup flour and salt.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into ungreased angel cake pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in.
Roll dough in 1-inch balls and roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. They will puff up a lot at first, then flatten out.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: crab and pork egg rolls(cha gio)
directions: Soak tree ears in hot water until they inflate, about 5 minutes.
Drain, rinse well and chop.
Soak cellophane noodles with cold water until pliable, about 5 minutes.
Drain and with scissors, cut them into 2-inch lengths.
Mix pork, crab, carrot, onion, salt, pepper, m.s.g, egg yolk, tree ears and noodles in a large bowl.
Coat each rice paper wrapper with hot water by using pastry brush.
Allow to stand a few moments to soften.
Place a good tablespoon of filling mixture into a rice paper.
Fold it up neatly (use egg white to seal).
Deep-fry the folded rolls in oil at 350° to 375° immediately until golden brown.
Place browned rolls on end in colander to drain off oil.
Serve hot with nuoc mam dipping sauce or without.

title: chocolate-caramel layer squares
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk in top of double boiler. Cook and stir constantly until caramels are completely melted. Remove from heat.

title: marinated fish steak
directions: In large dish or plastic bag, combine juices, oil and dill weed; mix well.
Add fish steaks.
Cover marinated steaks and place in refrigerator for
2 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Grill or broil until fish flakes with fork.
Frequently baste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 can sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf and put in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours; baste occasionally.

title: seafood appetizer
directions: Soften in cold water, dissolve over hot water.	Combine ingredients, adding gelatin mixture last.
Put in greased fish mold and use
sliced
almonds on top to look like fish scales. Use olives
for
eyes after it has been refrigerated overnight and unmolded.

title: skillet goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frypan.
Drain fat.
Push hamburger and onion to side.
Brown macaroni to yellowish-brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and roll into a ball; let chill. Put parsley flakes and chopped pecans on wax paper and roll tuna ball in it.

title: frozen slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze.
Serve with half Slush and half 7-Up.

title: date skillet cookies
directions: Stir and cook gently 10 minutes over low heat. Cool 5 minutes. Pour over Rice Krispies mixed with 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Shape into balls. Roll into flaked coconut.
Chill.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle the rice into a 13 x 8 x 3-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; pour over the rice.
Place the chicken pieces, skin side up, in the dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place a slice of margarine on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender, but not done.
Mix with soup and pour into a buttered 8 x 11-inch glass dish.
Top with cheese, then bread cubes.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in pan and mix with graham cracker crumbs covering bottom of pan.

title: international bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except grated cheese in ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. Serves 15.
Serve with Fritos or Doritos.

title: zesty cheese football
directions: Run pecans through medium blade food processor.
Mix with other ingredients (except chili powder).
Chill 15 minutes.
Form into flat football shape and sprinkle with chili powder, covering completely.
Chill to serving time.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Combine in bowl first 4 ingredients.
Beat and add chocolate chips and set aside.
Sift or mix the next 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat all ingredients together (dry and wet).
It will be runny.
Fill muffin cup 1/3 full with chocolate batter and add heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture on top. Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 24 cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat in 3/4-inch wide strips with grain.
Dissolve salt in warm water and add remaining ingredients.
Soak meat in mixture for about 2 hours, turning frequently so each piece is drenched. Place strips on paper towels for a few minutes.
Place on oven rack.
Cook at 120° to 130° for 8 to 9 hours with oven door slightly cracked open.
After cooking, turn off heat, open oven door and let air dry for 8 hours more.
Package in bags or jars.

title: tabuli salad
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over the bulgur; soak for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain well and add the tomatoes, parsley, pepper, chickpeas, green pepper, zucchini and carrot.
Mix the ingredients that were in the jar well.
Then mix all together and toss lightly.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, blending flavors.
Adjust fresh veggies according to availability and taste.
Garnish with black olives and Feta cheese.
Serve with wheat crackers.
Makes a large salad.
May keep up to 3 days.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch Bundt cake pan.
Combine cake mix, gelatin, oil, nuts, eggs, flour and strawberries in large bowl.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake 55 minutes.
Turn out to cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or plain.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and pack into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fish fillet in tomato sauce(heart healthy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place oil, half onion and parsley in baking dish.
Place fillets on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Contains 147 calories, 4 grams fat and 152 mgs. sodium.

title: pecan stuffed squash
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup broth.
Pour remaining broth in shallow baking dish.
Place squash, cut side down, in broth. Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.
In medium saucepan, over medium heat, heat reserved broth and margarine until margarine melts. Stir in stuffing mix, pecans and raisins.
Turn squash over, cut side up. Spoon stuffing into squash cavities.
Bake 20 minutes more or until squash is done, basting with broth after 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: o.j. soda
directions: Put the ice, orange juice and soda into a cup.
Mix until orange color is
gone.
Put ice in.
Let it rest for 5 minutes. Drink and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with electric mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer fruit tart
directions: Soften and spread cookie dough on a large pizza pan.
(Cook following directions on cookie package.)
tags: Philadelphia whipped cream cheese with strawberries

title: crispy marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of boiling water about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine carrots, onions and green peppers; set aside.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over vegetables; toss lightly with a fork. Refrigerate overnight.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: easy stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken breasts by enough to stuff and roll.
Make stuffing according to package.
Place equal amounts of stuffing in each breast.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Wrap with bacon.
Bake in pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with baked potatoes and salad.

title: squash and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Combine lemon juice and honey; set aside.
In a wok or large skillet, heat oil on medium-high.
Add squash, garlic and ginger. Stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Add the broccoli, celery and onion; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and quickly toss with the honey mixture.
Sprinkle with sunflower seeds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderate hot).
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and pumpkin thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Blend dry ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture, stirring until well blended.
Add raisins and pecans.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cookies may be iced when cool with a thin butter icing.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: spicy sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet; pour off fat.
Add beans, barbecue sauce and peppers.
Cook, stirring frequently, until bubbly-hot.
Serve over warmed hamburger buns.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Add zucchini.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix in gradually with the sugar, oil and egg mixture. Mix well.
Add pecans. Pour in two loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy pork
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces. Place in plastic bag with taco mix and shake until well coated. Brown in skillet in small amount of oil. Add salsa and marmalade; simmer for 10 minutes or until pork is done. Serve over rice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a bowl, mix cornmeal and flour.
Add all other ingredients except buttermilk; stir well.
Add enough buttermilk needed for your cornbread batter.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until done and lightly browned.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let set several hours before serving.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, broth, water, onion and garlic in Dutch oven. Add chicken, chilies, cumin, oregano, red pepper and cloves.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Cover with cheese and serve.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Place crust in 9-inch pie pan.
Turn under edges and flute. Place apples in bottom of unbaked crust; cover with caramel topping.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing well until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour this mixture over caramel topping. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Chill.
To serve, garnish with additional caramel topping.

title: dump salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into glass serving bowl. Chill and serve.

title: sour cream blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat baking mix, eggs, milk and sour cream with hand beater until smooth.
Stir in berries.
For each pancake, pour 1/2 cup batter onto hot grill.
Cook until pancakes are dry around edges. Turn. Cook other side until golden brown. Yield:
about 15 pancakes.

title: stew beef
directions: Cook beef until done.
Add carrots, potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushroom soup; simmer until done.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: hobo
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat off.
Add chopped onion, beans, corn and tomato sauce.
Cook about 5 minutes, then it's ready to eat.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Fix 2 cups Minute rice, using regular or wild rice.
Place in baking dish with the rice on the bottom, grilled chicken breasts next and then cooked vegetables. Top with good helping of Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake or microwave only long enough for cheese to melt.

title: summer squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop from a spoon into hot greased skillet.

title: avocado crab dip(servings:  4)
directions: Mash avocado with lemon.
Add crabmeat and mix gently.
In a separate bowl, combine next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Fold in avocado-crab mixture.
Chill before serving with tortilla chips.

title: hearty he-man turkey soup
directions: Cut turkey in small pieces.
Pour oil in skillet.
Add turkey. Saute over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until turkey is light brown.
Add celery, onions, carrots and green pepper.
Saute 8 to 10 minutes.
Add garlic.
Cook slowly over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour soup and chicken broth in a saucepan and stir over medium heat.
Add turkey, vegetable mixture, corn, peas, Brussels sprouts, broccoli, bay leaves and pepper.
Stir. Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaves. Stir.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions. Cut up remaining ingredients into bite sized pieces and mix in a large bowl with macaroni. Prepare dressing according to directions and pour 1-1 1/2 c. on salad.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Separate cucumber slices and onion rings.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Chill both mixes and toss together gently, shortly before serving.

title: top of stove meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 of the tomato soup with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 2 loaves.
In skillet, brown on both sides in shortening.
Cover and cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Top with the remaining soup, water and horseradish.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: graham cracker cheese cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot milk and put aside to cool.
Cream the cheese and then add melted marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream. Let set in refrigerator overnight (not freezer).

title: robert's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add some of the milk to mix well, then add remaining milk.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Cook in skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: creamy tacos
directions: In a slow cooker, add beans, chili, tomatoes and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Right before serving, add Cool Whip.
Serve over Fritos.

title: hershey's chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat oleo, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing to wire rack.
Press kisses into center of each cookie (if desired).
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
jello
with 1 cup of boiling water.
Use pineapple juice and
enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add pineapple, oranges, cranberry sauce, nuts and apples.
Mix well and pour in
pan
or mold.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until done.
Add soup, cheese, salad dressing, pimento and olives.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with asparagus spears.
Pour juice from can over top.
Top with 1 cup Stove Top crumbs.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions, olive and peppers. Spread thin layer on a tortilla.
Arrange 4 slices of meat on top of spread.

title: ripe olive cheese ball
directions: Fits on salad size plate.
Blend softened butter, cheeses, onion and olives.
Shape in ball and roll in almonds. Refrigerate.
This also freezes well.
Serve with crackers.

title: pikelets
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Add flour alternately with milk in which bicarbonate of soda has been dissolved.
Add melted butter.
Have ready a hot greased pan or griddle iron.
Put mixture in dessertspoonfuls in pan or on griddle iron.
Brown both sides, lift out and drain on absorbent paper.
Serve topped with jam and whipped cream for morning or afternoon tea.

title: deep dish peaches and cream
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding mix, butter, egg and milk.
Pour into 10-inch casserole (greased).
Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Place peach slices over batter. Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup peach juice with cream cheese.
Spread over peaches.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: roll-ups
directions: Muffuletta:
Drain black olives, green olives and pickled Italian vegetables, chopped very fine.

title: peach preserves
directions: Mix together in saucepan peaches, sugar, lemon juice and pineapple; stir, bring to full boil.
Boil 15 minutes on medium high.
Add 1 large package orange Jell-O (6 ounces) and boil for 5 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt the Hershey bars in a double boiler.
Add half large Cool Whip, then pour in cooked pie crust.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top, then chill for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in 1/2 pound chopped nuts.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Mix macaroni, mushrooms and pimento.
Melt the cheese, canned milk, onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix cheese sauce and macaroni mixture together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. May be topped with tomato slices, if desired.

title: california yeast rolls
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk and shortening until shortening is melted.
In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Gradually stir in hot liquid.
Add egg and stir well.
Mix in enough flour for kneading consistency.
Knead 5 minutes.
Cover dough and let rest 10 minutes.
Pinch off a small piece of dough and shape for rolls.
Place rolls in a greased pan.
When pan is filled, cover rolls and let rise in a warm place, free from draft, 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk (small amounts).
Beat well after each addition. Add flavoring and coconut.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease casserole or roasting pan (with a cover).
Put rice over bottom.
Thin slices of butter on rice (here and there). Chicken pieces next, salt and pepper, sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in two cups of hot water.
Pour chicken over all.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Rice should be moist, but now swimming in liquid.

title: ham loaf
directions: Form into a loaf and place in baking dish.
Bake while making sauce.

title: sangria(red wine punch)
directions: Chill one orange and one lemon for garnish.
Squeeze juice from other orange and lemon.
Place juices, wine, sugar and brandy in a large pitcher or bowl.
Stir to dissolve sugar; chill. Just before serving, divide mixture into 2 pitchers or pour into bowl.
Cut chilled orange into wedges.
Slice chilled lemon into cartwheels.
Core apple and cut into wedges.
Thread fruit on 2 long skewers to stand in pitchers or float in fruit bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled carbonated water.
Makes about 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Place Bunker Hill gravy and beef chunks in a skillet.
Stir in mushrooms, Worcestershire, sour cream, onion powder and black pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Cook on low setting for 8 to 12 hours.
Serves 6.

title: linguine and creamy clam sauce
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
Drain.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms and garlic. Cook until tender.
Stir in flour. Gradually blend in reserved clam liquid and half and half. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add clams, Parmesan cheese, sherry (if desired), parsley and pepper. Heat through.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked linguine. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream cheese and sugar and set aside.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions (on package).
Fold in cheese and sugar mixture and blend well.
Pour over cool crust in pan.
Mix in a saucepan sugar, cornstarch, jello, dash of salt and boiling water.
Bring to a rolling boil; stir often.
Remove from heat as soon as it comes to a boil.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Set aside to cool.
After mixture is cool, mix in strawberries.
Pour over filling. Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt slightly to mix. Stir in scalded milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 6 custard cups or a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; set in a pan of hot water (1-inch deep). Sprinkle a little nutmeg over tops.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or just until a silver knife comes out clean.
(Soft center sets as it stands.)
Immediately remove from oven.
Serve cool or chilled in same cups or dessert plates or unmold and serve.
Pass grape or other fruit juice to cover, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cheeses thoroughly.
Pat out in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 taco mix over top; refrigerate.
Cook hamburg; drain and crumble.
Put layer of ground beef on top of cheese mixture. Sprinkle a little taco sauce on.
Add layer of green pepper and onions, then a layer of cheese.
Sprinkle rest of dry mix sauce over top, then tomatoes last.
Serve with round corn chips.

title: connie's 5 bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Add brown sugar, salt, vinegar, dry mustard and catsup.
Add 1 can of each bean with juice.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour in an oven at 350° or in a crock-pot and simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs and margarine.
Place mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Brown bread crumbs lightly in margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before cooking.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, eggs, biscuit mix, sugar, margarine and vanilla in blender.
Cover and blend 3 minutes on low speed.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
(I use Pam or Mazola spray.)
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy pork tenderloin
directions: Combine the first five ingredients; rub over tenderloins. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Grill over hot coals for 15 minutes per side or until juices run clear or the internal temperature reaches 160°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill. Cut off the top of a round loaf of sourdough French bread.
Carefully hollow out the inside of the bread and cube it.
Fill bread with dip mixture. Pass chips, crackers and French bread for dipping.

title: classic french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container; refrigerate.
Shake dressing before serving.
Makes approximately 3/4 cup of dressing.
Contains 90 calories per tablespoon.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw broccoli and shred cheese.
Mix ingredients together. Pour in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, water, evaporated milk, rice, salt and pudding for 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla together in bowl.
Beat well.
Add to rice and milk mixture. Simmer 10 minutes more.

title: roast beef
directions: After washing meat, place meat in large casserole dish.
Pour water, Italian mix and sprinkle of pepper.
Place meat in preheated oven at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or until tender.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute onion in oleo until clear.
Drain.
Drain chicken and cut up in bite size pieces.
Add 1 cup cheese, sour cream, hot sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Roll biscuits as thin as possible.
Spread chicken mixture on biscuits.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes at 450°.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Boil chicken until done, mix with soup, Veg-All and half of onions in bowl.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then sprinkle the remaining onions on top.
Then brown a little.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake in greased 8-inch pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and crumble; set aside.

title: punch
directions: Dilute orange juice with the water.
Mix all ingredients and chill well.
If desired, float chunks of pineapple and fresh oranges on top.
Can be served plain or can add orange sherbet for a sweeter punch.
Makes 43 (6 ounce) servings.

title: hot southern corn muffins
directions: Heat
ungreased
muffin
pans
in
a
oven for 10 minutes.
Combine
cornmeal, soda and salt in large bowl; stir in pimiento,
cheese, onions, chiles and garlic.
Make a well in center of mixture.	Combine eggs, milk and corn; add to dry mixture,
stirring	just until moistened.
Spoon into prepared muffin
pans, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes,
until golden.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter fancies
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and mix. Pour over corn flakes-coconut mixture that is in a very large bowl, that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spray Pam on hands as needed while making mixture into balls.
Place on wax paper.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add enough flour to make a real stiff dough.
Knead well.
Roll out dough and cut with a cookie cutter.
Put a raisin on top and bake for about 10 minutes, or until done.

title: jim's lemon fluff
directions: Chill large mixing bowl in refrigerator. In another bowl, mix jello according to directions. Put in refrigerator just until it begins to set up. While jello is chilling, crush box vanilla wafers. Put layer in 13 x 9-inch baking dish, saving enough to sprinkle on top. Remove jello and beat with mixer for at least 5 minutes until most of large bubbles are gone; set aside. Pour chilled evaporated milk into the large chilled bowl. Beat on high speed at least 5 minutes until milk is thick and smooth. Fold in jello mixture, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice. Mix well. Spoon, don't pour, jello/milk mixture onto layer of crushed wafers. Sprinkle remainder of wafers on top. Refrigerate until firm, then enjoy! Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Roll in chili seasoning mix and pecans.
Chill.

title: blackberry pie filling for 9-inch pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through berries.
Pour into pastry shell; dot with butter.
Add top crust and decorate and perforate.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in a sifter 1/4 cup of the sugar, cake flour and salt.
Sift mixture 3 times.
Put whites into bowl of electric mixer and beat until foamy.
Add cream of tartar. Continue beating, gradually adding remaining sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Fold in vanilla and almond extracts.
Sift approximately 1/4 of flour mixture over the batter.
Fold in with rubber spatula.
Continue adding flour and fold after each addition.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in top part of double boiler.
Stir in vinegar; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add butter, onion and beets.
Place over hot water and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef vegetable pie
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients 15 to 20 minutes in heavy skillet. Remove to large bowl.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add water, gravy mix and seasonings; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables. Spread out pastry pockets as directed.
Add 2 tablespoons (or so) filling.
Fold over and pinch together.
Make 3 to 4 slits in back.
Brush with egg mixed with water.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: brushetta
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion, basil, and parsley to taste.
Mince garlic.
Mix together and add olive oil.
Mixture will be liquidly.
Spoon onto bread slice and top with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix altogether and fold in 2 cups sour cream.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with Italian salad dressing.

title: ham and cheese oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Mix in remaining foods.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch or 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes, or until omelet is set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare banana cake according to package directions for 2 layer cake.
For fillings, divide whipped cream or dessert topping in half.
Fold berries into half of the whipped cream.
Fold drained pineapple into the other half of the whipped cream.
In small saucepan, heat and stir fudge ice cream topping over low heat just until warm (not hot).
To assemble, using serrated knife, split each layer in half horizontally.
Place bottom of 1 split layer cake on a serving plate.
Top with strawberry cream mixture, spreading to edge of cake layer.
Place another split cake layer atop.
Spread with half of the warm fudge topping, letting it drizzle down sides.
Sprinkle with half of the nuts. Top with another split cake layer.
Spread with pineapple cream mixture.
Top with remaining split layer cake.
Spread remaining warm hot fudge topping atop cake, letting some of it drip down the sides of cake.
Sprinkle remaining chopped nuts.
Serve immediately or cover loosely with plastic wrap, placing a few toothpicks in top of cake so the wrap doesn't stick to topping. Chill 2 hours.

title: red beet (pickled) eggs
directions: Add vinegar and
sugar	to
red
beets in large bowl or glass jar.
Stir	until
sugar
is dissolved.
Add hard-boiled eggs and refrigerate at least 3 or 4 days.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in shallow baking dish and place one slice of cheese over each piece.
Stir soup and water together. Spoon evenly over chicken. Crush the stuffing mix coarsely and sprinkle over the top.
Evenly drizzle with butter or margarine. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done. Serve with rice.
It may be served with more hot cream of chicken soup sauce, diluted with milk, if desired.

title: chicken neapolitan
directions: Saute the garlic and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
After sauteing, remove from pan and set aside.
Cut chicken into chunks and dredge in flour.
Add chicken to pan, along with 2 more tablespoons of olive oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute chicken until golden, approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Add mushrooms and garlic to the chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Add the heavy cream; stir.
Cream will reduce; add more cream if necessary.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cookies do not spread.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese and crabmeat soup
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over hot water stirring constantly until thickened. Add cheese, stir until cheese melts.
Add tabasco and crabmeat Heat. Garnish with chives. Serve immediately.

title: butter icing
directions: Cream butter.
Sift in sugar gradually and mix until smooth. Add vanilla flavoring or chocolate and milk or cream to make desired consistency.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine cider and sugar in a large enameled pan or crock-pot. Tie cinnamon and cloves with cheesecloth bag; add to cider mixture.
Bring to simmering over medium heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Discard spice bag.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown rice and onion in oleo.
Stir often until slightly brown.
Dissolve beef cubes in hot water and add to rice and onion.
Place in Pyrex baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces and mix with the sauce in a saucepan.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat. Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in mixer bowl.
Add biscuit mix gradually, mixing well.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Shape as desired.
Roll in melted butter.
Arrange in a baking pan.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen.

title: ice cream
directions: Whip the eggs and add sugar.
Beat well.
Add Milnot and pudding mix.
Beat 5 to 7 minutes more.
Add the whipping cream or half and half.
Whip a minute longer.
Add vanilla or fruit of your choice.
Pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill a 1 gallon freezer.

title: apricot salad
directions: Pour pineapple (juice and all) in boiler and heat.
Add Jell-O; stir to dissolve.
Set aside to cool.
After it is thoroughly cooled, add buttermilk and pecans.
Mix well and add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour in dish and keep in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix together rice and cream of chicken soup.
Spread on bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: german kraut
directions: Cook the onion in bacon fat until lightly browned; drain. Combine all in frying pan.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.
Serve hot.

title: mary's pepper relish(no cook)
directions: Grind vegetables and mix together.
Add 1/2 cup salt and allow to stand 2 hours; drain.
Mix spices, vinegar and sugar.
Mix with vegetables and can, sealing tight.

title: oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a bubbling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and peanut butter; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: apple danish
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg yolk and milk and add to flour mixture.
Stir just until dough clings together.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll half the dough into a 15 x 10-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: strawberry pie(fresh)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, syrup and water together.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick and clear.
Add gelatin powder, stirring until
dissolved.
Cool.
Arrange
strawberries
to cover bottom of baked
pie shell.
Pour cooled gelatin mixture over strawberries and chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well in food processor.
Spread as desired.

title: cinnamon crispies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add molasses, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° (or until lightly browned).

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with Pam.
Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes, gradually add sugar beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together all dry ingredients, except nuts.
Fold in pumpkin mixture.
Spread into pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Turn onto towel that has been dusted with 4x sugar.
Roll in towel and let cool.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until soft.
Saute onion and butter.
Add flour, milk, seasoning and cheese.
Add carrots; put in a casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together flour, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add syrup, milk, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: texas wiener sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add meat.
Stir until meat loses color. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes. Spoon over hot dogs in buns.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, 1 Tbsp. milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
In a second bowl, stir pumpkin, pudding mix and spices into remaining milk.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.)
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve with remaining whipped topping.
Make 8 servings.

title: watermelon pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin until well dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate approximately 10 minutes.
Spoon into crust; return to refrigerator for four hours.
Garnish with additional topping.
Serves eight.

title: glorified rice
directions: You can substitute miniature marshmallows in the ingredients.

title: sausage pot pie
directions: Brown sausage.
Add 2 quarts of water to broth that sausage was canned in.
Bring to boil, add onion and potatoes, sliced. Then add dough.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Slice cookie dough 1/2-inch or 3/8-inch thick and line the entire pan with slices touching.
Whip together the packages of cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Spread cream cheese mixture over top of cookie dough.
Make another layer of cookie dough over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and then refrigerate.

title: country style steak
directions: Brown seasoned meat in oil.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Heat oil and saute garlic and onions until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil then cover and simmer over low heat 1 hour.
Saute sausage, or you may substitute ground beef, until brown and drain off fat.
Mix Ricotta and Mozzarella together in a bowl.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce on bottom of baking pan.
Arrange noodles with layer of cheese mixture, parmesan cheese, tomato sauce and meat.
Repeat process ending with layer of noodles and sauce.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the peanut butter with 2 tablespoons of milk until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop on foil or wax paper in balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: gino hot peppers
directions: Strip peppers into rings.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar.
Put salt, garlic and alum into a jar.
Pack jar with peppers tightly and pour vinegar mixture over peppers.
Seal jar and wait 30 days to eat.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Saute next 3 ingredients.
Cook rice. Mix all together; salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple pork chops and rice
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown well in butter (skillet).
Add pineapple and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender (about 20 minutes).
Move chops to one side, add water to salt.
Bring to a boil, stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: butter rum frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and syrup alternately to butter, beating well after each addition.
Beat in rum extract.
If necessary, add more sugar until proper spreading consistency is reached.

title: garden dew dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill several hours.
Serve over salad greens.

title: bean salad
directions: In colander, open and drain beans.
Mix in chopped onion, pepper and pickle.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper together. Bring to boil.
Pour over bean mixture.
Stir in oil.
Let set several hours before serving.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey in skillet until it falls apart.
Add green pepper and onion and cook until they become soft.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili mix.
Add water; cover and simmer until heated through.

title: sausage pie
directions: Skin and cook sausage meat, chopped cold cuts and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly and add to meat and cheese mixture.

Roll out dough and place in a large square or round pan that is slightly greased. Spread around pan and have leftover dough hang on side of pan. Pour mixture in dough pan and flip over leftover dough on side of pan on top of mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: south carolina cobbler(or poor boy cobbler)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put margarine in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat in oven until sizzling hot.
Heat cherry filling on top of range until bubbly hot.
Mix together flour, sugar and water.
Batter will be thin.
Remove baking dish from oven.
Pour half of batter into melted butter, add filling and drizzle remaining batter over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle a small amount of sugar on crust the last few minutes of baking.
Recipe can be doubled - use larger baking dish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into greased dish and put butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put in broiler in deep pan, oleo, water and soup mix.
Heat enough to melt oleo.
Add rice and chicken parts.
Cook for approximately one hour and 15 minutes, until chicken is done and slightly browned.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Grate zucchini and drain for 2 hours.
Add grated onion, mayonnaise, Old Bay, eggs and bread crumbs.
Dip in flour and fry in oil.
Chopped celery may be added.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain well.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix together and pour into greased muffin tins.
Fill about half full. Let rise about 20 minutes. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: orange waikiki
directions: In an 8-ounce glass mix juices.
Add ice cubes and fill glass with lemon-lime flavored soft drink.
Decorate with fresh orange slices.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan. Crumble. Cook hamburger and onion in bacon grease. Add to remaining ingredients. Cook slowly, the longer the better.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onion, jalapeno, cilantro and garlic in food processor until fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chop to blend. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, egg yolks, pineapple and nuts; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Stack cookies with mixture between as filling (use 3 cookies and 2 portions of mixture per serving).
Refrigerate on cookie sheet 3 to 4 hours.
Whip cream and sweeten to taste.
Cover each serving and shape into rounded ball.
Cover with shredded coconut.
Place each snowball on paper doily and return to refrigerator until serving time.
Then garnish with cherry or tiny red candles or holly sprig.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into small pieces and place in baking dish. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Mix with water and butter.
Pour over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in larger pan of hot water in moderate oven (350°) until firm, about 50 minutes.
Serve piping hot with cold vanilla ice cream.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Place all frosting ingredients, except vanilla and confectioners sugar, into small saucepan.
Bring slowly to a full rolling boil, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Quickly pour over cooled cake, allowing it to run down sides and set.
Frosting will harden very quickly.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 11 x 13-inch cake pan with nonstick spray.
Dip chicken in spread; coat with remaining ingredients. Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Prep time:
5 minutes.
Cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: hippeli cookies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Continue beating while adding sugar and lemon peel.
Mix in flour.
Drop by large teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies lightly with anise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
While still warm, bend cookies over wooden spoon.

title: chocolate twinkie pie
directions: Slice Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Set in bottom of pie plate, cream side up.
Slice 2 bananas on top of Twinkies.
Make chocolate pudding and pour over bananas.
Cover pie with Cool Whip.
Set for 1 hour or more in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, tartar and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Shape in rolls 2-inches in size and wrap in wax paper.
Chill.
Slice, as desired.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: snickers bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Spread 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While baking cake, melt caramels with margarine and milk over low heat. Pour over cake, then sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel.
Put rest of cake batter over this and bake 20 minutes more.
Good with ice cream!

title: potato casserole
