directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Do not bake!
Melt chips and margarine.
Cool.
Add eggs, nuts and then add marshmallows.
Divide into 3 rolls, wrap in waxed paper sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Put into freezer.
Cut in slices with electric knife while still cold.
After cutting, sprinkle with powdered sugar so pieces won't stick together.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat until creamy. Add remaining ingredients, pecans last. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at about 300° or 325° for 10 minutes or until cookies are barely brown.
Make cookies barely 1 teaspoon large when dropping raw dough.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix well (blueberries last) and bake in muffin tin or cups at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: chantilly cream
directions: Whip the whipping cream in chilled bowl with chilled beaters. Fold in sour cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla extract.
This is a topping that does not get watery for 2 to 3 days stored in refrigerator.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients with the exception of the flour and vanilla.
Bring ingredients to a boil on the stove, then set aside and allow to cool.
When cool, add flour and vanilla; mix well.

title: chocolate blender frosting
directions: Put in blender in order given.
Blend on medium speed until blended.
Blend on high until thick and creamy.
Stop and stir frequently.

title: peking roast
directions: With sharp
knife cut slots in roast; insert slivers of onion. Put meat in bowl and slowly drizzle white vinegar over it. Cover
tightly
and
refrigerate
overnight.
Pour
off vinegar before cooking.
Wipe with a damp cloth.
Put in heavy pan; brown in
tablespoons
oil.
Pour
2 cups coffee over meat.
Add 2 cups water.
Cover and cook slowly about 6 hours.

title: tropical glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Let cool to touch; peel and cut into 1/2 inch slices. Arrange slices so edges overlap in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo for crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Beat pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of second layer.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: lynn's meat balls
directions: Mix meat with spices.
Into meat and spices that are well mixed, add eggs, bread soaked in milk and onions.
Squish together and form large balls.
Put enough vegetable shortening and olive oil to cover bottom of pan, about 1/2-inch.
Simmer meat balls until done.
Set aside in large skillet.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 250° until brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix pineapple chunks, sugar, plain flour and grated cheese; pour in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and dab 1 tablespoon of margarine on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: noel shrimp bake
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter just until tender.
Combine with other ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup butter over.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: kentucky bourbon balls
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add nuts; mix well. Form into 3/4-inch size balls.
If too soft, work more confectioners sugar into mixture.
Place balls on a metal tray. Chill 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Place grated chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water.
Bring to 130°, stirring slowly.
Remove from heat.
Refill bottom of double boiler with cold water until it cools to 82°.
Refill bottom of the boiler with 85° water to maintain temperature while dipping balls.
Place each ball on fork.
Dip in chocolate until well covered.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Do not place in refrigerator.
Store in airtight container.

title: easter pizza
directions: In bowl, place in layers ham, cheese and pepperoni, ending with cheese.
Then scramble eggs; add milk and salt and pepper to taste. Pour egg mixture over layers so that egg is almost to top of layers.
Egg mixture will raise up above layers.
Bakes about 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350° with lid or foil.
Will be very hot. Let cool until room temperature.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Enjoy.

title: deep fried catfish
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Put meal, flour, salt and pepper into brown paper bag or bowl with tight fitting lid.
Wash fish; cut into pieces.
Dip fish into milk and egg mixture.
Put several in meal mixture at one time.
Shake well until well coated.
Heat cooking oil to rolling stage or until it boils when one piece is dropped in.
Cook until browned.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add orange rind and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thick.
Stir in pineapple and celery.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm, 3 to 4 hours.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add rice, beef broth and beef consomme.
Place in casserole dish and cover.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Coat biscuit quarters in sugar mixture and put in a greased Bundt pan. In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine and nuts.
Cook over low heat until sugar is melted.
Drizzle this over biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand about 15 minutes to cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake as directed.
Bake in 11 x 16-inch pan.

title: play dough
directions: Heat water with salt in saucepan until salt dissolves.
Remove from heat; add oil and dry ingredients.
Store in jar or plastic bag.
Keeps best in the refrigerator.

title: lo-cal salad dressing
directions: Beat egg thoroughly; combine the dry ingredients and add to the beaten egg.
Add water, vinegar and Sucaryl, beating well. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Serve on salad greens.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In large frypan, brown sausage well.
Add green pepper, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Add eggs; scramble well.
Place 1 cup of mixture in middle of each shell.
Sprinkle cheese on top; roll up shell.
Place in microwave until heated. Top with salsa, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 burritos.

title: farmers salad
directions: Slice onions 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick and separate into rings. Dice as much celery as you like.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and pour over onions.
This is better if ice cubes are placed on top of salad to cool and crisp it.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water; stir to dissolve.
Add cold water, pineapple and blueberries in syrup.
Place in glass bowl. Chill until set.

title: kahlua
directions: You will need 2 quart bottles, dark colored glass.

title: jim's jogger juice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for at least 3 hours or immediately serve over ice.
Great for people on the run!

title: beans and franks ole
directions: In saucepan, combine beans, tomato sauce, brown sugar, dry mustard and hot dog slices.
Heat on medium for 10 minutes. While bean mixture is heating, place 1/2 cup corn chips into 4 serving bowls.
Add 1 cup hot mixture over corn chips.
Place cheese slice or grated cheese on top of each serving.

title: appetizer franks
directions: In medium saucepan, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add wieners; let come to a boil.
Turn on low heat and cook for 25 minutes. This will make about 50 appetizers.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut nuts and fruits in small pieces; roll in flour and then add to other ingredients that have been well mixed.
This makes a 5 pound cake.
Bake 4 hours at 375°.
If two smaller cakes are preferred, bake 2 1/2 pound one for 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked mash squash(a thanksgiving day favorite)
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes until smooth.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream, onion salt and pepper.
Beat into potatoes until fluffy.
Adjust seasoning to your taste.
Place in greased, 2-quart casserole.
Cool and cover tightly.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Combine ground beef with rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Pile lightly into pepper halves.
Place in a large baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce on top of each pepper.
Cover tightly and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until peppers are tender, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked bluefish with sesame seed
directions: Blanch lemon rind for 5 minutes and pat dry.
In skillet, brown sesame seed.
Remove.
Cook ginger in 2 tablespoons butter. Add remaining butter and lemon juice.
Cook until brown.
Add sesame oil, mustard, cayenne pepper, soy sauce and salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Pour over fillets.
Sprinkle scallions and cover.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt 2/3 of the margarine in a 10 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Place hash browns in pan. Sprinkle chopped onion on top. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.
Mix sour cream, soup, salt and pepper. Spread on top of cheese.
Melt remaining margarine and toss with corn flakes.
Top casserole with corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (with jackets) until almost done.
Slice a layer of potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Crumble half of bacon on top and use half of cheese.
Layer again and pour melted butter over top.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back when touched.

title: italian holiday cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, lemon peel, vanilla and salt. Add eggs and 2 cups flour; mix well. Turn onto a floured surface and knead in remaining flour (dough will be soft). With a floured knife or scissors, cut into 20 pieces. With

hands, roll each piece into pencil shapes. Cut "pencils" into 1/2-inch pieces. In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 350°. Fry pieces, a few at a time, for 2 minutes per side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Place in a large bowl. Heat honey to boiling; pour over cookies and mix well. With a slotted spoon, spoon onto a serving platter and slowly mound into a tree shape if desired. Decorate with candy sprinkles. Cool completely. Yield: About 15 dozen.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cream seasonings thoroughly into butter.
Spread a part of this butter mixture on the bottom of a casserole; arrange on mixture 18 large mushroom caps, open side up.
Dot each cap with some of the remaining butter mixture until all is used.
Add the cream and salt and pepper.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then serve at once in casserole in which they are cooked. Serves 6.

title: pineapple 2 cake
directions: Mix all together; pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: martha washingtons
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Form into small balls. Chill.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add sauce, salt, pepper and tomatoes in hamburger.
Add the other ingredients together, except for lasagne.
Layer beef mix about 1 cup in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Alternate beef, lasagne, cheese and layer again.
Top with some Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Watch so cheese don't burn.

title: sugar-free cocoa mix
directions: Combine all.
Store in airtight container.
For each serving add 3/4 cup boiling water to 1/3 cup mix.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture and combine. Divide dough in half and place on sheets of parchment paper.
Roll each half into a log about 1 1/2 inches.
Refrigerate until firm, 2 hours or overnight.
Cut logs into 1/4-inch and place on pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix dry jello and cream cheese together with a fork.
Mix according to package directions.
Chill until rather firm.
Whip until light and foamy.
Add pineapple.
Whip the cream and fold it in.
Put cherries and nuts on top.
Chill until firm.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until no longer pink. Add soup and seasonings. Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes. Meanwhile, slice the top third off the bread. Hollow out bottom half of loaf, leaving a 3/4-inch shell. Spread butter on cut side of bread. Place loaf on a baking sheet and broil until lightly browned, this will not take long. Spoon beef mixture into shell. Arrange cheese slices on top. Broil until cheese is melted. Replace bread top. Cut into 2 to 3-inch slices.

title: snapping turtle stew
directions: Cut up the meat in 1-inch cubes.
Brown in butter or margarine.
Place remaining ingredients in a stew pot, add water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 30 minutes. Add the turtle meat and cook slowly for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening,
add sugar.
Cream well, add eggs one at a time and
beat
well
after each one has been added.
Add spices and salt
and
mashed
prunes.
Add
soda to sour milk. Add alternately with
flour
to creamed mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in greased and floured baking dish.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Place dandelion blossoms and 4 quarts water in kettle or Dutch oven; boil 30 minutes.
Strain to remove blossoms, then strain through cheesecloth into a large stone or glass jar.
Let stand until cool, then dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add yeast mixture, raisins, sugar, lemon and orange, cut in small pieces, to dandelion liquid.
Let stand for 2 weeks, stirring each day. Strain through cheesecloth several times until clear.
Add the rum.
Pour into 3 clean wine bottles; seal with cork or screw cap. Makes 3 bottles.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and milk.
Beat well. Then add flour, corn meal and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender (do not salt).
Cube chicken; put in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Spread dressing over mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over top of dressing.
Next pour chicken broth over dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly (15 to 20 minutes).
Serves 12.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and let set for 1 hour. Add applesauce and thawed raspberries.
Pour into mold which has been rinsed in cold water to prevent jello from sticking.
Use Cool Whip for topping when being served!

title: easy roll pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening until it looks like meal.
Add water, vinegar and egg all at once.
Mix lightly.
Roll on floured board.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour over steaks and marinate for 5 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Enough for 4 steaks. Makes the tenderest steaks.

title: devil's food pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right-side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until jello is dissolved.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling; let congeal.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl. Pour over cherries and sugar. Use 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: beef and potato pie
directions: Boil the potatoes for about 10 minutes.
Drain and place in the bottom of casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, grate some cheese over the top.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and vinegar in a buttered 4-cup glass microwave dish; cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 12 to 17 minutes on Medium High (Roast) or until candy forms a firm ball in cold water (240°).

title: callahan's carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to the sugar mixture; blend well.
Add grated carrots and chopped nutmeats. Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into two greased 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: spanish shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and seasoning and blend.
Add soup stock and cream.
Cook until thick and add catsup.
Add shrimp last.
Pour into buttered baking dish and cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Makes 40 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, food coloring and liquid chocolate.
Mix well and add buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and add vinegar and soda.
Stir until well blended.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 layers.

title: rum or bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate with rum or bourbon and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well and form 1-inch balls and roll in 10x sugar and place on cookie sheet until cool.

title: barbecued bologna
directions: Slice bologna almost through, after removing skin, and tuck slice of onion between each slice.
Heat remaining ingredients to boiling point.
Pour over the roll.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until done.
Baste often.

title: blt bites
directions: With a small sharp knife, cut the top off of each tomato. Scoop out the pulp with a
small spoon and place each tomato cut side down, on paper towels to remove liquid.
Discard pulp.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into tomatoes.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can top it with buttered bread crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
It can be made ahead of time and refrigerated for a couple of days.

title: sweet broccoli salad
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Drain and set aside to cool.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar until sugar is dissolved. In large bowl combine onion, sunflower seeds, raisins, celery, broccoli and bacon.
Pour sauce from small bowl over and mix well. Ready to serve or may be refrigerated.

title: orange jello salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple to a boil. Remove from heat. Add Jell-O. Stir to dissolve. Add buttermilk. Mix well. Cool to room temperature. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated eye of round
directions: Combine and pour over roast.
Cover and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Turn 3 to 4 times.
Remove from marinade.
Towel dry and roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Slice thin for sandwich.

title: brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients, except nuts until smooth.
Pour into plate; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: date roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and salt; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. When mixture comes to a boil, add the dates and continue cooking, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°). Pour into bowl and cool until lukewarm. Beat until thick and creamy, then add nuts. Pour onto a wet cloth.
Shape into a roll and wrap in a damp cloth. Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.

title: italian delight
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook on low.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add to meat mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pineapple pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in unbaked pie shells and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line with paper baking cups or grease (not oil) 12 muffin cups.
In medium bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Make a white sauce by melting butter over low heat.
Add flour and milk, stirring until smooth.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Place noodles, peas and ham in casserole.
Pour white sauce over and mix thoroughly.
Top with bread crumbs and bake until bread crumbs are nicely brown.

title: laura bush's oatmeal chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. With electric mixer, cream butter and both sugars. Beat in eggs, one at a time, then beat in vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and oats. Slowly beat until blended. Stir in walnuts, chocolate and cherries. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet covered with parchment paper. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar and cinnamon.
Use on sandwiches, between apple or pear slices.
May be used on toast or graham crackers.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: mary kaye's pan apple cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla to cream mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease
pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onions	in
a
skillet over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate. Beat milk, eggs
and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes and top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until knife
inserted
in
center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening, butter, cream cheese and peanut butter until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. In a small bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to cream mixture, blending well.
Add vanilla. Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot ham and potato dinner
directions: Layer the ingredients in order.
Alternate these layers until crock-pot is full.
Put crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan an amount of sliced potatoes, onions and carrots for desired number of servings.
Lightly salt and pepper these.
Arrange the desired number of pork chops over the sliced vegetables.
Cover the chops with the undiluted soups and cover the pan with foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue to bake a few more minutes to brown slightly.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until rolling for about 3 minutes. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to cool. Serves 24.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Rinse and drain.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in greased sheet pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes.
Yields 24 squares.

title: beef-n-cheddar
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add sauce.
Roll out dinner rolls and put in meat mixture.
Top with cheese slices.
Crimp edges. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: jimmy deans
directions: Brown meat until no longer pink.
Add seasonings and cubed cheese until cheese is melted.
Spread on cocktail rye slices. (Two loaves of rye.)

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight. Drain and rinse in hot water.
Cook in 3 quarts of water. Chop the onions, garlic, carrots and parsley. Add 1/2 lemon.
Cook ham 2 to 3 hours, cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Remove 2 cups cooked beans and run through blender. Pour back into soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Also add 2 cups water.

title: ham and cheese brunch
directions: Cover bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 the bread cubes.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese over bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over casserole.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Knife in center should come out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Saute bacon until crisp. Dice celery, carrots, onion, pepper and garlic and saute with crisp bacon.

title: cheesy lasagne
directions: Sauce:
Brown ground beef; pour off grease.
Add in large pot the ground beef, Ragu, stewed tomatoes, onions, peppers, garlic and Ricotta cheese.
Let simmer.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients together until clear. Set aside until cool.
Add a dash of salt to the egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Add mixture. Continue beating until creamy. Add 3 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Top on favorite pie.

title: 2 hour rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, sugar, eggs and water.
Add the butter.
Mix the salt and flour; mix all together.
Let rise until double.
Cut to size; let rise again.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a casserole at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until brown and drain.
Add pepper, macaroni, tomatoes and garlic salt.
Let cook all together, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Take off stove and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Mix up well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: phoney abalone
directions: Pound chicken breasts until flat.
Marinate 36 hours in clam juice.
Roll in cracker crumbs; saute until done.

title: mom's hot rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add eggs, lard, sugar , salt and flour.
Knead and let rise.
Make into rolls and bake at 375° to 400°.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine soups, cream, salt and onion.
Add to potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Transfer into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: apple slices
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Mix egg yolk with milk and stir into flour mixture.
Roll half of dough out and fit into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Arrange apples on dough.
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour with sugar and pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Roll out rest of dough to cover apple mixture.
Seal edges.
Brush with egg white.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar icing.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and pudding.
Blend in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Arrange cherries on top.
Refrigerate for an hour or this can be served immediately.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat
oven
to 350°. Grease baking pan. Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping;
press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake
minutes;	cool.
Top
with
nuts and chocolate pieces. In	medium saucepan melt caramels with water over low heat;
stir until
smooth.
Remove
from
heat.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces
to	within 1/4-inch of pan edges;
sprinkle with reserved oat mixture. Continue baking 15 to 18 minutes or until
light brown.
Chill
until chocolate
is set. Cut into bars.

title: clam chowder (or new england chowda!)
directions: Saut sausage; cook thoroughly. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons butter. Saut onions. Add clam juice, seasoning and potatoes; cook for 5 to 6 minutes. Cover potatoes with water and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes until potatoes are tender. Add half and half and evaporated milk and clams; heat through, but don't boil (makes the clams tough!). You may thicken the chowder with flour and water mixture if you like a thicker soup. Add a few drops of Tabasco to add flavor. Enjoy. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and chopped onions; drain fat.
Combine meat mixture, beans and tomatoes.
Add diced pepper, some chili powder and some hot sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno beans
directions: Chop bacon, brown and drain.
Brown hamburger and add onion, then fry until onion is limp.
Remove and drain all grease.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in a large casserole and bake in 350° oven for at least one hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken cassserole
directions: Cook and de-bone the chicken.
Cut into bite sized pieces.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for a few minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into slightly greased Pyrex pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into wedges and top with vanilla ice cream.
Very rich; good served warm.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and pat with paper towels to remove excess oil.
Mix all remaining ingredients except cheese. Pour 1/2 of cornbread into greased skillet.
Top with meat and then cheese.
Add remaining cornbread.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut together, then roll out.

title: pink delight salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with cherry juice; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Let stand until cool.
Sift flour, soda, sugar and salt together and add to dates and water. Add egg and melted butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: company chicken
directions: Run hot water over dried beef.
Pull apart.
Wrap chicken in bacon.
Place in long baking dish.
Put beef over chicken.

title: golden slushy punch
directions: Boil the water and sugar; cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.
Add 2 large bottles of soda pop.

title: russian mushrooms
directions: Saute the mushrooms and onion in the butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Cover with sour cream and top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts and browns (about 15 to 17 minutes).
Serve as a side dish.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Pour orange juice and soy sauce over wings.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and ginger.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour more.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use mixer and beat cream cheese, coloring and flavoring. Add 1 cup of powdered sugar for each ounce of cream cheese. Mixture should be stiff.
Pinch off and put in mold.
Dump out on waxed paper and let set for about two hours.
Also can be served frozen.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour on top of mixture in Bundt pan.
Add rest of mixture to pan.
Swirl with a fork.
Bake at 350° between 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: green beans italiano
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine beans and water.
Cover. Microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring once.
Drain well.
Add garbanzo beans, pimento, olives, olive oil, oregano and garlic powder; mix well.
Cover and cook again for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple bavarian
directions: Cook together egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and crushed pineapple until thick.
Add lemon gelatin.
Stir well and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar and fold into cold mixture. Put crushed crackers in buttered round or square glass cake pan, saving some for top.
Pour pudding on crackers and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill 24 hours.
Can also be frozen.

title: fruit pie
directions: Blend with mixer the cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Put into pie shell.
Top with the oranges, kiwi fruit and pineapple around or any fruit, canned or fresh, you desire.
Cover and refrigerate a couple of hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Peel, pit and slice peaches.
Puree them in an electric blender.
In a large bowl, combine egg yolks and 6 tablespoons of honey mixture.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.

title: easy "old fashioned" bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Allow to come to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 to 2 hours, or until thickened and potatoes are tender.

title: eckrich sausage and cabbage and ranch style beans
directions: Saute onion with garlic and sausage.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer. Put lid on pot and cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Sift dry ingredients.
Add along with pumpkin and eggs to oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican hot dish
directions: Fry meat and onions; then add all other ingredients, except Doritos.
Heat until cheese melts.
Alternate layers of meat mixture and Doritos, starting with Doritos.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot sherbet
directions: Run the apricots through a sieve or a blender.
Stir in sugar, milk, lemon juice and apricots.
Freeze in ice cream freezer. Makes 1/2 gallon.
Delicious.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, milk, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Form into 24 meatballs; brown in oil.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until done; remove meatballs.
Add green onion; cook until tender. Add cream cheese, water and mushrooms.
Heat over low heat; stir until smooth.
Arrange meatballs over hot noodles; cover with sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Boil sugar and water until it spins a thread.
Add cinnamon, vanilla and pecans.
Stir like crazy.
When pecans are coated well, pour out onto waxed paper.
Break apart, if needed.
Good, good!!
Yum yum!!

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, soften cream cheese, then beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Mix in milk.
Then add vanilla.
Fold in juice from lemons with large spoon. Spoon mixture into crust. Chill for 3 hours.
Spoon cherry filling on top and chill until smooth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes, add butter, sugar, milk, salt and lemon rind; blend well.
Scoop some and put a marshmallow into it.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place in a buttered baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: cheddar and tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken, cook until browned.
Stir in cumin and cayenne pepper.
Cook 1 minute. Add chicken broth, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt until hard ball stage. Beat egg whites until soft peaks.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites, beat until forms soft peak.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice cabbage up (like for coleslaw) and put in pan.
Brown hamburger and add onion and garlic powder. Sprinkle rice over cabbage and then sprinkle browned hamburger over cabbage.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Mix 2 cans tomato soup with 1 can of water and pour all over top.
Do not mix. Cover.
Cook at 375° for about 2 hours or until cabbage is cooked.

title: chicken stew
directions: Clean the chicken and cut into pieces.
Boil with shallots, little ginger, salt and 3 cups of water in a saucepan.
Take the chicken out, fry or bake until lightly brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add cooked spinach and finely chopped water chestnuts.
Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with artichoke hearts.
Fill with spinach mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: trimmed-down taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 10-inch deep dish style microwave-safe pie plate, combine ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once to break meat apart.
Remove from microwave and drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce, salsa and chili powder; mix well and set aside.

title: skinny soup
directions: *Suggestions:
carrots, zucchini, potatoes, cauliflower, 1 green pepper, cabbage, green beans, broccoli, etc., whatever you have.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk
and oleo to a boil.	Boil rapidly 11 minutes,
stirring	occasionally.
Add rest ingredients.
Stir well until Marshmallow Creme and chips are melted. Pour into 9 x 12-inch buttered pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble cookies and set aside 1 cup for later use.
Mix remaining cookies with butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 tub Cool Whip topping (with mixer).
Spread mixture over cookies in pan.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Spread pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour (to allow pudding to set up).
Remove and spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with remaining cookies over Cool Whip for decoration.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans in a glass pie plate.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; mix well.
Pour over beans.
Grate cheese and spread on top.
Slice green onions and ripe olives and sprinkle over top of cheese.
Top it with your favorite salsa sauce; optional fresh tomatoes on top.
Serve with crackers or chips. Super dip.

title: no-peek stew
directions: Place the beef in a casserole.
Mix the onion soup, mushroom soup and 1 can water and pour over the beef.
Cover tightly with a heavy lid or foil.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours or until beef is tender.
Do not peek.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunchy onion layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 3-quart glass bowl as listed.
Serve with Ranch buttermilk dressing just before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook meat (fry), onion, rice and meat together.
Pour in tomato sauce, cook all together, as long as you feel it is done.

title: reuben dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine in bowl cream cheese, sour cream, sauerkraut, corned beef, onion, catsup, mustard and Swiss cheese.
Put in ovenproof dish and bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove, cover and bake 5 minutes more until golden.
Serve warm.

title: spinach and cream cheese
directions: Follow directions on package for cooking spinach.
Mix cream cheese, onion and spinach together.
Reheat and eat.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased, covered casserole for 2 hours or until thickened.

title: baked beans
directions: Use 2 1/2-quart dish 8 x 8-inch.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Empty half of pork and beans into bottom of greased casserole dish. Combine sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle half of mixture over beans. Top with remaining beans, then rest of sugar mixture.
Sprinkle on bacon, then catsup.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat together ingredients, except pecans and pie pastry.
Mix in the pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pan. Bake until set and pastry is browned at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 + hours until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all except pumpkin and eggs well in electric mixer or blender.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
Pour into 2 greased pie pans. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Chill before cutting.
This pie makes its own crust!

title: salt maps
directions: Add water to flour and salt, 1 tablespoon at a time, until the right consistency.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and pickling lime for 24 hours.
Rinse in cold running water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, food coloring and pickling spice.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers.
Boil for 30 minutes. Take up and put in hot jars with lids.

title: meat loaf or meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the ground beef, mango, onion, eggs, flour and Sloppy Joe mix.
Form into loaf or meatballs. (Spread Brooks tangy ketchup on meat loaf.) Fill pan 1/4 way with water.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: With mixer, mix together (except apples) ingredients until like corn meal.
Place on top of 2 to 3 inches of peeled, cored, thinly sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: saute veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and large baking sheet.
Stir together flour, sugar and orange peel in mixing bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cranberries.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
When done, take potatoes out of peelings.
Fix for creamed potatoes and put back in jackets.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Put back in stove and brown.

title: granola squares
directions: Cook and stir brown sugar, Karo syrup and peanut butter until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a pan and chill.
Cut in squares.

title: punch
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water; stir until dissolved, then add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into a larger pan and add lemon juice, pineapple juice and cold water.
Freeze about 6 hours before you serve.
Set out of freezer.
Add ginger ale after you put punch into punch bowl.

title: hot water sponge cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and hot water all together until foamy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook in 13 x 9-inch pan or muffin tins. Bake 15 minutes at 315°.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
When mixture boils, reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes or until cranberries burst.
Mash berries a bit.
Pour out and chill.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine blueberries, cornstarch and sugar replacement in bowl. Toss to coat and pour into pie shell. Bake at 425 for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix Ragu, sugar, hamburger and 1/4 Ragu jar of water (if you use Prego, add 1/2 jar of water).
Just cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan with Ragu mixture. Layer the noodles, cottage cheese, Ragu and Mozzarella cheese twice.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle the 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over the top; let set for at least 15 minutes.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: You will also need a 3-quart saucepan, a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and a candy thermometer.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In large bowl, crumble corn bread until very fine.
Add onions, radishes, bell pepper and tomato.
Fold the mayonnaise into the salad.
Better when prepared the day before.

title: stuffed sole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion, shrimp and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Add crabmeat; heat through.
Sprinkle fillets with salt, pepper and paprika.
Spoon crabmeat mixture on fillets; roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine the soup, broth and water; blend until smooth.
Pour over fillets.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover; bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley; return to the oven, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.
Good!

title: chicken breast with honey-wine sauce
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
mix the wine, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Add
chicken pieces; stir to coat and marinate 1 hour in refrigerator.
Drain chicken.
Reserve marinade.

title: rice pudding(top of stove)
directions: Cook rice.
Add eggs, canned milk, sugar, regular milk and vanilla.
Heat.
Add cornstarch mixture to thicken some.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, powder and nutmeg; set aside.
Mix and beat sugar, zucchini and egg.
Add oil, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir flour mixture into batter. Fold in walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and canned milk and cook to a soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and add the Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: 24-hour pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into thin slices.
Wash and soak in lime water overnight.
Wash well and soak in salt water four hours.
Drain and soak in cold water two hours.
Drain again and bring to a full rolling boil in alum water.
Drain and rinse.
Cook 30 minutes in vinegar, spices and sugar.
Pack either hot or cold.

title: frogmore stew
directions: To boiling water, add sausage that has been cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add seasoning and bay leaves.
Let this boil about 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are about three-fourths done.
Add corn and cook about 5 minutes.
When this returns to boil, add shrimp.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, checking to see if shell and shrimp are separating.
When shrimp is separated from shell, turn off heat and let all ingredients sit for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain off water and serve.
Feeds 6 adults.

title: chalupas
directions: Mix chicken with sour cream, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin, 1/2 pound Monterey Jack and 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese, shredded.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter; pour in bottom of casserole dish.
Add rice. Place chicken on rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and water.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Mix together.
Let sit for 10 minutes. Drop from teaspoon on baking sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chops in mushroom sauce
directions: Brown the meat in a skillet with oil until it is golden brown. Place the meat into a casserole dish and pour mushroom soup over the top.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: door slammer
directions: Mix together the soup, rice and milk in casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of mixture, skin side down.
Bake at 250°, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Turn chicken over once during cooking.

title: tropical jello
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to Jell-O to dissolve. Drain pineapple. Save juice. Add water to make 1 cup. Add to Jell-O. Chill until syrupy.
Save 1/2 cup Jell-O. Add pineapple, banana and marshmallows to Jell-O in the bowl.
To Cool Whip, add 1/2 cup Jell-O.
Add sour cream and gently blending, swirl on top of Jell-O and fruit. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt almond bark; mix with remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Cut French bread into 8 thick slices.
Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, combine strawberries, bananas, sugar and cinnamon.
Put in greased baking dish and top with prepared bread.
Sprinkle with Cinnamon Sugar.
Bake in 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Melt the butter, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour over noodles and toss lightly.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Pour rice on bottom of baking dish.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Lay pieces of cut broccoli on rice also.
Mix 3 cans soup plus 3 cans of water.
Pour mixture over chicken in baking dish. Cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: coffee dessert
directions: Melts marshmallows in double boiler, add hot coffee; blend and set aside to cool.
Whip
cream and fold into cooled mixture, then add cherries, dates and nuts.
Sprinkle generously finely crushed graham cracker crumbs into a large dish, then pour in the mixture, covering top with crumbs and (if desired) chopped nuts.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with cream topped with a cherry.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: hot turnip slaw
directions: Peel turnips and slice.
Cook in boiling water until tender; drain.
Fry bacon until crispy, then break in small pieces.
Leave about 2 tablespoons of drippings in pan.

title: creamy egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: smore bars
directions: Beat butter and sugar together and then add flour. Using a 9 x 9 pan, grease it and then press graham cracker crumbs into pan. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes on low. Spread melted chocolate on top and then put marshmallows on and broil, but watch closely. When the marshmallows tan, then take it out. Let it cool, and then enjoy!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except crumbs.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cherry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water and bring to hard boil.
Beat egg whites to fairly stiff, adding 1 tablespoon Jell-O at a time. Pour hot syrup over mixture.
Drop from spoon.

title: niki sullivan's chicken almondine
directions: Bake at 325° covered with foil for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: nachos plus
directions: Put tortilla chips on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Make sure they don't overlap.
Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Sprinkle the olives, bacon pieces and green onion.
Bake in a 400° oven for 2 to 3 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Transfer to a serving platter.
Serve with sour cream or taco sauce.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fresh fruit refrigerator cake
directions: Blend together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add prepared fruit.
Line narrow, oblong 8-inch spring-form cake pan with wax paper.
Cover with fruit mix and layer with wafers.
Chill in refrigerator 6 hours or longer.

title: creamy frozen fruit cup
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Set aside 18 oranges and 9 cherry halves for garnish.
Chop remaining cherries.
Add pineapple, pecans and cherries to the cream cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining oranges.
Line muffin cups with paper or foil liners.
Spoon mixture into cups; garnish with cherries, oranges and mint. Freeze until firm.
Can also put in a 10 x 10-inch dish and freeze, then cut into squares.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Thaw frozen artichokes and green beans.
Rub chicken breasts with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Arrange chicken in 3-quart casserole.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet.
In remaining hot drippings in skillet, over medium heat, cook green onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; gradually stir in milk and water until smooth; stir in ketchup, rosemary, bouillon and 3/4 teaspoon salt; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly.

title: r v chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle rice evenly on bottom of pan.
Mix chicken soup and water together and pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix evenly over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: wesson brownies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs, add oil, chocolate and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave low cholesterol banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, egg substitute and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Stir in bananas, nuts and remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf glass dish.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack.

title: old fashioned hot water cakes
directions: Pour hot water over meal and mix.
Add enough cold water to make consistency desired.
You may like individual drop cakes or thin cakes.
I also use less cold water and make into small pones. Fry in hot skillet with about 1/2 bacon drippings or other fat. Brown one side, then the other.
Great with vegetables or fish!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix the flour 'n sugah together...add milk to which the beaten aig yolks hav bin put...place over boilin' watah, stirrin' til mixture begins to thicken...then kiver 'n cook til well thickened.
Add coconut 'n pore in a baked pie shell.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry gelatin until well blended. Add 1 cup boiling water. Mix well. Blend cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and sugar into first mixture. Put in 10 x 5 inch glass dish. Chill in refrigerator until set. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and beat into creamed mixture.
Add water; toss dates and nuts with flour and add to batter.
Place in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle in graham cracker crumbs.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk.
Top with remaining ingredients and press down in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hoecakes
directions: Mix well all ingredients together, except the oil.
Heat the oil for frying in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drop two tablespoons of hoecake batter into skillet.
Brown 2 minutes per side until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and jelly; fold in thawed Cool Whip. (Lasts in refrigerator a long time.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook the green beans; drain.
Add milk, soup and pepper.
Add 1/2 can onions. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with 1/2 can onions and pimientos. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in a bowl and add boiling water. Stir to combine and dissolve sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast and egg.
Add flour; knead and pat into shapes of roll desired.
Place on a greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fillets de sole, vin blanc
directions: Marinate the fillets in lemon juice for at least 15 minutes, then lay them in a buttered flat casserole.
Sprinkle finely chopped onion (or chives) and herbs over the fish.	Mask with mushroom soup diluted with Sherry.	Dot with butter.
Salt and pepper lightly.

Cover the surface with a sprinkling of cheese. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes, or until fish is opaque and sauce bubbles and starts to turn a golden brown. Serves 4.	Hot French rolls should be served with the fish to sop up the last drop of sauce.	A dry Chablis, plus a green salad, goes well with this dish.

title: bean and pea salad
directions: Combine vegetables and salt.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix until smooth. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Place in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: potato and sausage soup
directions: In large kettle brown sausage, onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except potatoes and cabbage. Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cabbage and cook 20 minutes longer.

title: quick and easy camp stew
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook over low heat for about 2 hours, or until potatoes are done.
May be eaten then or refrigerated overnight.
Heat and serve.

title: reuben dip
directions: Combine cheeses, sour cream, beef and sauerkraut in medium saucepan.
Cook on medium until melted.
Add a little milk to thin, if necessary.
Serve hot with rye chips or Melba toast as dippers.

title: "rosettes"
directions: Thin to suit taste.
I like mine just to catch on iron; more tender.

title: perky punch
directions: Put all liquids in bottom of percolator.
In top, put the brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Perk and serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot beef tostados
directions: Pour jar of picante sauce over roast in the crock-pot.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 6 hours or until done.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Add 2 cans of refried beans to broth in crock-pot. Stir in cut up meat and cook 2 more hours on low setting.
Serve on tortillas with lettuce, tomato, cheese and taco sauce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits
into fourths.
Roll in 3/4 cup sugar mixed with 1 tablespoon
cinnamon.
Put in buttered Bundt pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon with butter.
Pour over bread and bake 15 minutes.
Turn out warm.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread each tortilla with cream cheese and dressing mix in a thin coating.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables on top.
Roll up and slice with sharp knife or dental floss into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Refrigerate.

title: almond tea
directions: Warm teapot by rinsing with small amount of boiling water. Place tea bags in teapot; pour 2 cups boiling water over tea. Cover and steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar, lemon juice and flavorings; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 quarts water; stir.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve over ice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix cut up chicken with spices and sour cream in bowl.
Use mixture to fill tortillas and roll up and place in casserole dish (greased).
Chop onions and green peppers.
Saute in oil.
Add tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour on top of tortillas and top with cheese.
Bake for 25 minute at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Add vanilla and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add sifted flour and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and pack into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cabbage and onion and place in medium casserole dish (greased with butter).
Mix soup, egg, mayonnaise and melted butter.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix crushed crackers, butter and grated cheese.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: special eggplant parmigiana pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out crust onto greased cookie sheet as thin as possible and bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.

title: marshmallow-cereal bars
directions: Grease cake pan with butter.
Place butter and marshmallows in microwave bowl.
Microwave uncovered on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until mixture is melted and smooth.
Stir in cereal.
Press mixture into pan using a buttered spoon.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: apple-black walnut cookies
directions: In a 12-cup mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium speed about 30 seconds.
Add half of the flour, the granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour. Stir in oats, apple, walnuts and raisins.

title: tropical cheese log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and pineapple, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into log.
Serve with sesame crackers.

title: cabbage and corn dish
directions: In a large electric skillet, fry bacon.
Remove from grease. To grease, add all ingredients except bacon.
Cook on high heat 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over cabbage and serve.

title: easiest ever pecan sticky buns
directions: Chop 1/4 cup pecans and set aside.
Reserve the remaining 1/2 cup pecans to use whole.
Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch square baking pan.
Roll out bread dough on lightly floured surface to 18 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush the rolled-out dough with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle with the chopped pecans and the 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Add remaining whole pecans, the 3 tablespoons brown sugar and the syrup to the remaining melted butter in pan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Spray 10-inch tube pan with a release agent (Pam).
With electric mixer, blend dry cake mix and gelatin. Add eggs, apricot nectar and oil.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.
(This is a moist and delicious cake with an unusual flavor.)
If desired, add glaze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and 1/2 jar dried beef.
Mix with softened cream cheese and Accent.
Shape into ball and wrap all other dried beef around it.
Refrigerate.

title: glorified squash
directions: Mash squash in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 4.

title: u.m.w.'s chickenetti for "360"
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
(Hint:
Cook 6 or more chickens in large pot, well covered with water.
Lightly salt the broth.
When thoroughly done, remove chickens and cook remainder of the chickens in this broth.
This method gives a richer broth and more flavorful chicken.)
Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients reserving 5 1/2 to 6 cups cheese for topping.
Put in 15 baking pans.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift salt and sugar into flour. Blend in lard. Add milk, stiffening dough. Roll until smooth. Cut 1/2-inch thickness. Stick with fork. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir and pour in graham cracker pie shell.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine
beans,
onion,
sugar	and
ketchup.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes or at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix together well and add the cereal and chopped nuts.
In mixing bowl, combine salad oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 400° oven.
Batter may be kept in refrigerator up to 3 weeks and used as needed.

title: spinach lasagna roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook noodles as directed on package; drain, rinse and cover in cool water until ready to use. Then remove from water, lay flat on paper towels and pat dry. After noodles are dry, lay flat on a cutting board, side by side.

title: company broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli as package directs except cook only 4 minutes. Drain. Place in greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over broccoli. Pour mixture of soup and evaporated milk over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until onions are crisp and brown.

title: michael's mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Make sauce of soups, tomatoes and cheese.
Layer casserole with tortillas, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 onions and 1/2 sauce. Repeat with other half of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Crush chocolate wafers and mix with butter. Then spread the mixture into the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Beat eggs, cream cheese
and vanilla until smooth.
Add melted chocolate squares by	swirling
into the cream cheese mix.
After it is poured into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes. Cool.
Melt chocolate
chips and add sour cream to them.
Ice the cool cheese cake.

title: easy yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well.
Roll on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sunny's christmas avocado salad
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 package jello.
Stir to dissolve and cool.
When cool, blend with mayonnaise, sour cream and mashed avocado (or put all in blender and mix).
Rinse jello mold with cold water and fill.
Chill.

title: artichoke hearts appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar.
Add flour, soda and fruit cocktail with juice.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut dip
directions: Drain sauerkraut and chop a bit.
Reserve some liquid for thinning dip, if desired.
Mix mayonnaise with slightly softened cream cheese. Add sauerkraut and mix well.
This dip is very good (and unusual) served with carrot and celery sticks and assorted veggies.
Also good on Triscuits.

title: key lime pie
directions: Stir 3/4 Cool Whip into a bowl.
Add condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring.
Place in pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with remaining Cool Whip.

title: herley grilled potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add celery; cook until tender.
Stir in oregano, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cutting not quite through, slit potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Place each potato on a piece of foil large enough to wrap potatoes.
Drizzle about half of margarine mixture into slits.
Insert a half slice of onion into each slit.
Drizzle with remaining margarine.
Bring edges of foil together; seal securely with double foil.
Grill over hot coals 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: the byrd's easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Add yeast rolls.
Mix together dry vanilla pudding, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over rolls.
Let set out overnight.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 25 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and milk.
Drizzle over rolls and let sit 15 minutes.
Turn out onto platter and drizzle remaining glaze over other side.

title: blueberry cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda. Cream butter. Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Stir in dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries. Spread mixture on well-greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: *Or 4 cups mixed dried fruit.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the powdered sugar and butter 5 minutes on medium speed. Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour, beating 3 minutes. Add the lemon extract and vanilla, then 2 more eggs and 1 cup flour. Beat 3 minutes. Then add 2 more eggs with 1 cup flour. Beat 5 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes or until done.
Cool 30 minutes in pan. Dust with powdered sugar while cake is warm.

title: chocolate zucchini loaf
directions: Cream well oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, grated zucchini, milk and chopped nuts.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken breasts in orange sauce
directions: Season and brown chicken breasts in a small amount of fat. Remove from skillet.
Mix flour, sugar, mustard, orange juice, cinnamon and ginger together.
Stir into drippings.
Bring to a boil and return chicken to sauce.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender.
You may add orange pieces or pineapple chunks and heat just before serving.
Serve with rice and green peas.

title: kentucky chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: jimmy dean sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen balls. Can be frozen uncooked.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Cook the broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in a buttered casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine Crisco, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° about 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Place in large saucepan.
Add undrained vegetables, water and seasonings.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add cheese and salsa, if desired.

title: seven layer banana split cake
directions: Cut margarine into flour until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Beat powdered sugar, egg whites and softened margarine until smooth.
Spread on cooled layer.
Drain pineapple.
Spread over second layer.
Slice bananas and distribute over the pineapple.
Slice the strawberries and spread over the bananas.
Spread the whipped topping over the strawberries.
Sprinkle the nuts over the whipped topping layer. This serves 12 to 15.

title: one minute frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk; slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Beat exactly one minute. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool; beat until desired texture is achieved.

title: taco shells
directions: Heat 8-inch skillet on medium-low heat just until hot.
Grease skillet with vegetable oil if necessary.
Pour scant 1/4 cup of batter into skillet.
Immediately rotate skillet until batter forms very thin tortilla about 6 inches in diameter.
Cook tortilla until dry around edges, about 2 minutes.
Turn and cook other side until golden, about 2 minutes longer.
Makes about 8 tacos.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and oregano.
Line bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish with half of shells.
Top with half of meat mixture.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over meat; then top with remaining taco shells.
Spread remaining meat on top and put the shredded and Monterey cheeses on top.
Bake 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-vanilla wafer dessert
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Melt chocolate; add vanilla and add to batter.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and salt.
One-half cup of chopped nuts may be added. Spread half of crushed wafers in a buttered shallow pan.
Spoon on chocolate mixture 1 inch thick.
Sprinkle on remaining crumbs. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Cut in squares to serve.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: single lime and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add sugar, pineapple, lemon juice, salt, pecans, marshmallows and cottage cheese. Refrigerate.
When partially set, fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream.

title: cheese-grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in salted water until done and thick.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and garlic cheese until melted.
Add milk and beaten eggs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle grated cheese on top. Place cooked sausage or Canadian bacon slices on top.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and melted margarine.
Then add milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Slice off top of bread; scoop out chunks to form a sort of bowl and save chunks.
Put in filling.
Place top slice on loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
Use the chunks of bread as dippers, or use your favorite crackers.
A great crowd pleaser!

title: harvard beets(good for diabetics)
directions: Mix all ingredients except beets and cook until thickened and clear.
Add beets.
Cook until heated through.

title: lemon bread with poppy seed
directions: Mix all together and beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in 2 greased and floured bread loaf pans for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate bark candy
directions: Melt bark and peanut butter together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: bacon or ham soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring broth to boil.
Add 3 cups of sliced celery, onion, celery leaves, thyme, black pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Place half of the vegetables with some of the liquid in a blender; puree.
Return to saucepan and bring to boil. Add barley and simmer, uncovered, until barley is almost tender, about 25 minutes.
Add 2 cups celery and simmer until barley and celery are tender, about 3 minutes.
If reheated at a later time, add water if needed.
This recipe may be doubled.
Yields 4 servings.
Fresh celery makes broth a meal.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in 1/2 stick butter and oil.
Add shrimp; saute until pink.
Season with salt.
Cover and keep warm.

title: baked kraut recipe
directions: Drain all ingredients thoroughly.
Fry bacon crisp, then drain on paper towel.
Fry chopped onions in bacon grease until golden brown and drain on a paper towel.
Drain 2 cans kraut and broken up whole tomatoes and put in mixing bowl along with bacon, onion and 1 cup brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients and transfer to baking dish. Bake for hour in 350° oven.

title: gail's banana pudding
directions: Whirl milk, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and flour in blender. Transfer to double boiler; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until thick.
Do not scorch.
Alternate layering vanilla wafers in a casserole dish (larger than 2-quart) and bananas.
Pour pudding over.
Top with meringue.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: chicken carbonara
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat and cook chicken.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add onions, bacon and peas, stirring occasionally until onions are tender.
Add wine or broth and cook 1 minute.
Stir in alfredo sauce.
Return chicken to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes and sprinkle with pepper.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together.
Boil until thick and then put into cooled pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Take egg whites and make meringue for top of pies.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Boil zucchini 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Mix zucchini, onions, parsley, cheese, garlic, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and eggs. Heat 1/2 inch olive oil in skillet.
Drop zucchini mixture by large spoonfuls into oil; cook until browned on both sides. Drain.
Yields 6 to 8 fritters.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix grape juice and milk.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Fold in blueberries.
Put into 2 baked shells.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar well, then add the egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk.
Use small amount of flour to coat blueberries, then add to mixture.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for about 17 to 22 minutes.

title: jimmy gomes' favorite jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Set aside and let cool.
Add to cake mix the oil and eggs, one at a time, then the Jell-O.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together sugar and flour; stir into beaten eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix and then pour into pie pans. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This mixture will form its own crust.

title: hade swedish spice cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 6 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add baking soda, then add flour 1 cup at a time to mix well.
Place dough in cookie press, using flat bar design. Cookies are done when edges are lightly browned and cookies are still soft.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in the water and mix with hands until soft.
Pat a small amount back and forth between hands until flat and round.
Fry in 1 cup shortening until brown. Sprinkle warm bread with powdered sugar or serve warm with honey.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Squeeze all liquid from the spinach; chop onions and water chestnuts.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and soup mix.
Fold in spinach, onions and chestnuts.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together well. Mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, baking soda, salt, carrots and raisins together. Add sugar mixture to flour mixture. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until lightly brown, about 40 to 45 minutes. Cover with a cream cheese icing and crushed pecans.

title: vieno marsyla's finnish coffee bread
directions: In warm milk, dissolve small amount of sugar with dry yeast. Combine remaining sugar, salt and spices and add to yeast mixture. Fold in 1/3 of flour, then 1 egg, repeating until all eggs and flour are worked in.
Knead melted butter in.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Divide, roll and braid into loaves.
Place on greased baking sheet and let rise to double in size.
Brush with one whole beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion together. Add cheese and green tomatoes with chilies and heat over very low heat until cheese is melted. Stir often. Add chili powder. Eat with snack crackers.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: mixture for flowers
directions: Mix small amount of water with ingredients and mix well; then add remaining water.
