Water plants good 2 days before using this, then apply this and use this every 4 to 6 weeks as directed.

title: pea and macaroni soup
directions: Take medium pot, put oil to cover bottom.
Add small amount cut onion, small pieces cut bacon and let brown.
Add salt and pepper, parsley and tomatoes.
Let cook on medium heat 15 minutes. Add peas and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook macaroni, drain.
Add macaroni to bowl and add soup over (sprinkle with Parmesan cheese for added flavor).

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix in bowl other ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Do not cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Cook 1 cup rice.
When meat is done, tilt pan and spoon off excess oil.
Use this for gravy over rice.
Serves 8.

title: peach or strawberry tart
directions: Put crumbs on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix fruit, sugar and lemon juice together.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over crumbs. Sprinkle top with more crushed cookies.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours. So refreshing.

title: banana upside-down cake
directions: Beat the butter, eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar together until it turns a creamy white; put in refrigerator overnight.
Cut up bananas in bottom of pie crust.
Put filling in.
Put pineapple on top of filling and put Cool Whip on top of it.
Put nuts, coconut and cherry in middle of pie.

title: holiday salad
directions: Put gelatin in deep bowl; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add sour cream and beat until well mixed.
Add pineapple or berries, juice and all.
Add nuts.
Stir until mixed. Pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix everything, except pecans and bananas, in a bowl.
Add pecans and bananas.
Stir.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Soak onions in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.,

title: minestrone
directions: Heat the oil and saute the onion, garlic, carrot and celery for five minutes.
Transfer these ingredients to a large pot.
Add the beef broth, oregano and cabbage.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add the juice from the tomatoes.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces and add to the soup.
Add beans, peas and macaroni.
Simmer for 10 minutes until macaroni and all the vegetables are cooked. Serve with Parmesan cheese and bread or crackers of your choice.

title: purple potato salad(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Cut cool potatoes into bite size pieces.
Combine in large serving bowl with shredded cabbage.
In small mixing bowl, combine Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix, milk and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Stir in bacon bits and pour over potato-cabbage mixture.
Best when served immediately at room temperature, but may be stored in refrigerator and served cold.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Then add eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle orange slices with flour to chop.
Cook in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.
During the last 30 minutes of baking time, lay a sheet of foil over the top to keep the cake from browning too much.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in 350° oven.
Remove; pour batter over butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and vanilla together and cream.
Add the oatmeal and the sifted dry ingredients to the creamed mixture. Put 3/4 of batter in a 10 x 13-inch pan that has been greased. Melt the chocolate chips in the milk.
Pour over the batter.
Drop the rest of the batter by teaspoons over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Put over spaghetti.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat a 9 x 5 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pan with vegetable oil or vegetable shortening.
In large bowl, using a hand mixer, whip together banana, oil, eggs and water.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts (if desired) to banana mixture and mix. Stir in baking soda and baking powder quickly and then mix.

title: chicken pie casserole
directions: Debone chicken and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, pepper and milk; pour over chicken and butter.
Heat soup in 2 cups chicken broth and pour on top of casserole.
(Optional:
One package frozen or 1 small can sweet peas and carrots may be added, if desired.) Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: jello salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jell-O over cottage cheese, then add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix and serve.

title: florence's fruit bars
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
On 2 cookie sheets, shape bars in 2 rows 1/2-inch thick, 1 1/2-inches wide and full length of pan.
While baking, dough will become irregular in shape.
When about half done, push back in shape with metal spatula.
Cut in diagonal pieces with a sharp knife while hot. Take off cookie sheet and cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Crush
pretzels and mix with butter and sugar.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch
pan
and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or browned; cool. Mix
topping, cream cheese, and confectioners sugar and pour
over crust.
Add
boiling
water
over gelatin; add the strawberries. Chill
until
syrupy;
pour
over
layer
2 and chill.

title: browned butter frosting
directions: Heat margarine or butter over medium heat until delicate brown. Mix in powdered sugar. Beat in vanilla and milk until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water. Mix with remaining ingredients. Freeze. Stir several times to distribute fruit evenly. Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving. May be refrozen.

title: spinach cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cover chicken, onion, celery and 2 teaspoons salt with water and cook until chicken is tender. Bone chicken and cut in small pieces. Reserve 1 1/3 cups broth and combine with soup, tomatoes and chiles and 1/2 teaspoon salt; heat. Cut tortillas in 1/2-inch strips and soft fry. Place a layer of chicken, tortillas, cheese, onion and heated sauce in baking dish. Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 250° for 20 minutes; lower to 200° and continue baking for 40 minutes.

title: party pink punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and grenadine. Stir well.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Just before serving, add two quarts ginger ale.
Yields 24 (4 ounce) cups.

title: large peach cobbler
directions: In a large pan, melt 1 stick of margarine.
Set aside.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine and mix with cake mix.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour peaches with juice in pan.
Spoon cake mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown and when a toothpick that is inserted comes out clean.
Serve with ice cream.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Mix together and shape into a log.
Roll in slivered almonds or chopped pecans.
Chill.
Serve on tray with crackers of your choice.

title: my meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except soup.
Form into a loaf and place in roasting pan.
Pour soup over meat.
Bake 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Split muffins and spread mixture evenly on each half. Freeze on cookie sheet until frozen.
Cut each frozen half into quarters. Place pieces in a plastic bag and keep frozen until ready to use.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together in pint jars, adding vinegar last. Cover and shake to blend well.
Store, uncooked, until ready to use.
Keeps at least 1 month.
Yields 2 cups.

title: sweet spiced walnuts or pecans
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat together egg white and water with a fork. Add nuts; toss to coat. In a small mixing bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and
salt. Sprinkle sugar mixture over walnuts (pecans); toss to coat.
Spread nuts in prepared baking pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes. Spread on waxed paper. Cool. Break into pieces. Store in an airtight container. Makes 7 cups nuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together using milk to rinse soup cans of extra soup.
Place in 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add sliced cheese or grated cheese to top and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas relish
directions: Mix and boil all ingredients, except Certo.
Remove from heat and add Certo; let cool until thick.
Stir occasionally to keep peppers mixed.
Pour in sterile jars; seal with wax.

title: strawberry pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar together.
Beat eggs until light.
Add milk and mix well.
Add butter.
Heat 8 or 10-inch frying pan hot enough for pancakes to brown quickly.
Pour batter into frying pan in desired size; brown on both sides. Remove pancakes to large plate and heap with strawberries.
Roll pancakes with strawberries inside.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; garnish with crisp bacon and whole unstemmed strawberries.
Keep finished pancakes warm.
Makes about 5 large pancakes or 10 small ones.

title: german sauerbraten(slow cooker)
directions: Wrap 2 bay leaves, 2 whole cloves, 1 teaspoon mixed pickling spices in cheesecloth.
Add to sauerbraten.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low.
Last hour on high.
Add 3 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup cold water.

title: country casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Brown meat.
Add vegetables.
Cook until liquid is almost gone.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Put into baking dish. Add 1/2 stick of margarine (melted) and Cheez Whiz to Veg-All mix.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top of mixture.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Make up the pudding using the milk.
Line the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with vanilla cookies.
Put a layer of sliced bananas on top.
Add 1/2 of the pudding and another layer of bananas.
Arrange more cookies around the edge of the bowl. Add the rest of the pudding and spread to cover to the edges. Chill for several hours and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mince onion in broth.
Add cheese and margarine.
Put in Ro-Tel brand tomatoes and peas.
Cut chicken breasts in smaller pieces.
Add spaghetti.
Stir well.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Debone the salmon.
Flake salmon and add remaining ingredients in order given above.
Mix lightly.
Shape into loaf and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until loaf is browned.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cook chicken in butter.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Parmesan cheese and place chicken on top.
Reserve pan with drippings.
Add flour to drippings in skillet.
When flour is dissolved, add milk and seasonings.
Stir constantly.
When mixture is thickened, remove from heat and add Mozzarella cheese.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italiano meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef in a large skillet.
Drain. Add green pepper and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in water, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese over the bottom of the frozen pie shell.
Add 1/2 the meat mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese over this and layer remaining meat and Parmesan cheese.
Bake on a cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a full boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and quick oats; stir well.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoons.
Let cool, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook green pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, garlic powder and mustard.
Blend well.
Stir in baked beans; blend well.

title: chicken sunday dinner
directions: Spread clean rice in buttered 2 1/2-quart size casserole.
Lay chicken on top rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix all over chicken.
Cover with the soup and water.
Cover with lid.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: quickie pot pie
directions: Put bottom crust in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put 3 slices cheese on crust.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl.
Pour mix into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese, then crust. Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: scallop stir-fry
directions: Melt butter in skillet or wok. Saute scallops
in melted butter for 3 minutes. Add sliced mushrooms and cook for 2 more minutes. Pour in teriyaki sauce and cook 2 additional minutes. Stir in cashews just before serving. Serve over favorite rice.

title: chop stick tuna
directions: Combine soup and 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup of noodles, dash of pepper and remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan slices
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add
unbeaten egg.
Blend well. Add
flour, soda and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, prepare cake according to package directions.
Cut baked cake into 4 layers.
Turn cut-side up and trim off brown layer to leave cake open and porous to allow topping to sink into cake.
Spread coconut mixture between layers and on top.
Let stand at least 3 days in refrigerator.
Coconut mixture is a glaze and may have to be spooned on while cake is chilling.

title: roasted rosemary potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into eighths.
Rinse in cold water; drain and pat dry.
Put potatoes into a large casserole dish, making sure potatoes are not crowded.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Toss and bake in a hot oven (400 to 450°) until potatoes are tender and thoroughly browned.
Taste for seasonings. Delicious served with beef, veal or chicken dishes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Be prepared to double next time!!!

title: meat-cheese potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan heat cheese and milk, stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat. Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Cover and bake until hot through.

title: tom's spinach fandango
directions: Brown meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms and garlic, cut up fine.
Add spinach and cook until mixable.
Mix celery soup and sour cream into hot ingredients.
Put in roaster or casserole dish and cover with shredded cheese.

title: good stuff
directions: Fold altogether; chill overnight or several hours.
Use coconut if desired.
Omit nuts, if desired.
Keeps well.

title: instant potato candy
directions: Combine potato flakes and water in mixing bowl.
Beat until mix holds together and looks like mashed potatoes.
Start adding confectioners sugar, a cup at a time.
Continue adding until mixture can be formed into a ball.
Roll potato dough to a rectangle 8 x 12-inches.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll, starting with 12-inch side.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Refrigerate. Makes 20 to 24 slices.

title: grandmas date roll
directions: Mix the dates and marshmallows.
Pour milk over them and mix well. Add part of the crumbs and nuts.
Divide into two rolls and roll in remaining crumbs.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Rolls get better as they age.

title: easter lily cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and flour.
Roll out small amount of dough and cut into circles.
Place circles on foil covered cookie sheet.
Put 1 tsp of apricot jam in the upper center of each circle.
Fold the sides of the circle over to make the lily. Press down firmly.
Preheat oven to 375.
Bake 15 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle cookie with powdered sugar.

title: cheese in coffee
directions: Crumble cheese into a cup of coffee.
The cheese will melt and may be spooned over a split biscuit or a piece of toast.
The coffee will be given a satisfying flavor, but it takes more time to clean the coffee cups in the dish washing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water cook until thick - add few drops red food color and strawberry jello.
Cool.
Spread the bottom of pie shell with cream cheese and milk.
Fill shell with strawberries. Pour glaze over all and chill.
Top with whip cream. To serve: Try this pie with fresh fruit peaches - etc.

title: chocolate almond snowdrops
directions: Cream the shortening with 3 tablespoons of powdered sugar. Stir in flour and cocoa.
Add almonds.
Roll into teaspoon size balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Mix rice, meat, water, onions, salts, garlic powder and pepper. Shape mixture by rounding tablespoonfuls into balls. Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2). Stir together remaining ingredients. Pour over meatballs. Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Place apples in baking dish and sprinkle with white sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over water and cover with flour mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: acorn squash soup
directions: Melt oil or fat in heavy skillet.
Add flour; stir constantly over low heat until dark brown, but not burned.
To this roux, add seasonings, stock to make sauces, gravies, gumbo or whatever.

title: spicy sausage and vegetables
directions: Remove wrapping from meat and cut into 1/4 inch pieces.
Brown meat, onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add can of diced tomatoes and mixed vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer just until vegetables are tender (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Cook the squash in water with herbs and bouillon cubes.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add to squash and puree in a processor.
Return to pan.
Add broth, soy sauce and cooking wine.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
If the soup is too thin, thicken with 1 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch moistened in 1 to 3 tablespoons water.
Serves 4.
Serve warm or cold with a dollop of sour cream or yogurt.

title: peanut bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Combine in separate pan the sugar, oil, vanilla and peanuts, stirring only to moisten.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in pans before removing.

title: sweet potato dressing
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until lightly browned.
Add ground beef and sausage until browned.
Add sweet potatoes and bread crumbs until dry.
Bake in a 375° oven until top is lightly browned.

title: bananas foster
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise then halved.
Melt butter in a flambe pan or attractive skillet.
Add sugar, cinnamon and banana liqueur and stir to mix.
Heat for a few minutes.
Place banana quarters in sauce and saute until soft and slightly browned.
Add rum and allow to heat.
Ignite.
Allow sauce to flame until it dies out, tipping pan in circular motion to prolong flames.
Place ice cream in individual bowls.
Cover with 4 pieces of banana. Spoon hot sauce over top and serve immediately.
Serves 4. Cooking time is 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Spoon individual portions onto salad greens.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Measure cocoa, sugar, cream, syrup, butter and salt into a heavy saucepan, about 1 1/2-quart size.
Stir until blended, then bring to a boil over moderate to high heat.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Place meat in covered casserole.
Top with dry onion sour mix and cream of celery soup.
Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours. About halfway through baking, start to shred meat and stir to mix soups with meat.
Continue to bake, shredding and stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns for sandwiches or makes a good topping for noodles or baked potatoes.

title: pumpernickel rye bread
directions: Stir yeast into water and let stand.
Stir in other ingredients, until stiff.
Knead until elastic.
Allow to rise and punch down and form 2 loaves.
Allow to rise, brush with cold water.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wedding punch
directions: When almost ready to serve, place lime sherbet in punch bowl. Then pour over the pineapple juice, stir well.
Then add the ginger ale and mix again.
Serves about 25.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Toss the sauerkraut, celery, bell pepper and pimento together in a medium size Pyrex dish.
Put in a saucepan the onion, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour this boiling mixture over ingredients in Pyrex dish.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: busy lady pickles
directions: Put cubes in jar (1 gallon) and cover with vinegar, salt, alum and pickling spice.
Let sit for 6 weeks, pour off vinegar.
Add 8 cups sugar.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Mash dough in pan like a crust. Cook as directed on package. Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, dressing mix and sour cream. Spread on croissant crust.
Top with your favorite grated veggies. Top with grated cheese.
(I gently press down on top after I finished to help veggies from falling off.)

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Mix well. Shape into 2 balls. Roll in pecans; wrap tight in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 3 hrs.

title: almond butter crunch wheel
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch cake pan with foil and butter liberally.
(Do not use nonstick pan.)
Combine all ingredients in 10-inch skillet.
Heat to boil over medium heat and boil 5 to 6 minutes. The mixture will be amber.
Pour into pan and let set and cool for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and break into pieces.

title: italian quiche
directions: Bake pie crust 5 minutes to set; then pour ingredients into shell and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: lazy bone cabbage
directions: Saute meat in skillet until browned.
Drain.
Add rice and onion mix to meat, stirring well.
Slice cabbage into large baking dish or casserole.
Spread beef mixture over cabbage.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Add sweet potatoes and beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Combine dry

ingredients; add alternately with buttermilk. Grease and flour tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts over bottom of pan; pour in batter and top with remaining pecans. Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli; do not overcook and drain well.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and top with chicken.
Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Stir well and spoon over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: eggplant-spinach casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and slice to approximately 1/8-inch thick slices.
Blot dry on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients (except Hunt's sauce) and grated Romano cheese.
Sandwich this mixture between 2 slices eggplant.
Lightly brown on frypan and arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread Hunt's sauce over all and sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet to form crust.
Layer hash browns, meat and cheese over crust.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over all.
Bake at 350° until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend with fork until well mixed.
Makes 2 double crusts.
This dough keeps up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Whip milk and vanilla pudding until it thickens.
Line bottom of bowl with honey graham crackers.
Slice bananas over the crackers and cover with the pudding mix.
Repeat until all the mix is used.
Slice bananas on top.

title: tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water 10 minutes.
Drain, melt butter in top of double boiler over direct heat.
Stir in flour, then mustard.
Add milk, salt and pepper and stir over boiling water until smooth and thick.
Arrange potatoes, tuna and onions in alternate layers in a greased 2-quart casserole dish (I make 2 layers each; can add other can of tuna for richer dish).
Pour sauce over all and bake for 45 minutes.

title: icing for red velvet cake
directions: Cook milk and flour until thickened.
Set aside and cool completely.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add cooled milk mixture and continue beating until very fluffy.
Finely chopped nuts can be sprinkled on top.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°; grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onions; drain and stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour in plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: perfect custard
directions: Put eggs and vanilla
in bowl.	Beat in sugar and salt. Stir in milk.
Pour
mix into 8 (5 ounce) custard cups.	Place cups in shallow baking dish.
Pour boiling water in dish about an inch deep.
Bake
at 325° for 30 minutes.
Put coconut into mixture if so desired.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook on low heat for several minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer noodles, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and meat in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Note:
Enough for 1 pie, except fruit is enough for two pies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add scalded milk while hot to shortening, then add salt, sugar, potatoes and beaten eggs.
Mix together in electric mixer or by hand.
Add yeast cakes to water and dissolve and add to first mixture.
Add 3 cups of flour, sifted and beat.
Gradually add rest of flour.
If electric mixer wil not take all flour, add by hand, beating well.
Do not knead.
Add 1 cup raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Mix in and place dough in large container in the bottom of refrigerator.
Let rise 2 to 4 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over chopped vegetables.
Mix vinegar, oil, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Mix 1 tablespoon tea mix with 1 cup hot water.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut up cabbage in bowl.
Chop up good.
Cut your tomatoes up in bowl too.
Add Miracle Whip.
Salt and pepper to taste.
That's it!
You can put as much Miracle Whip and tomatoes as you want too.
This was my grandmother's recipe.

title: cornetti
directions: Mix yeast and warm water to dissolve.
Add sugar and 3 tablespoons flour and let stand until bubbly.
Add salt and remaining flour.
Knead really well until smooth.
Cut and form cornetti and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mandelbrot
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Divide batch in half.
Add vanilla to one half and the cocoa to the other.
Shape into 4 loaves, using equal amounts of each batch; place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until slightly browned.
Take out of oven; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Turn the slices on their sides; put back in oven for toasting, about 10 minutes.
Cool and eat.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and beat until you have the right consistency to frost pumpkin cake or carrot cake.

title: elizabeth welch's gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and molasses; add dry ingredients (sifted together) alternately with soda dissolved in 1/4 cup hot water.
Knead until well mixed ball; chill several hours in covered bowl.
Roll out on floured board or waxed paper. Ct out favorite cookie cuter.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes (on greased cookie sheet).
Use Royal Icing for decorating.

title: ham-it-up snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into four long rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangle. Spread ham slices with mustard; sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle; press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each roll into 5 pieces, forming 20 slices in all.
Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Can be reheated.
Wrap in foil; heat at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time, covered and refrigerated.

title: microwave dessert
directions: Combine dry cake mix, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour pie filling into 8-inch glass baking dish; spread evenly. Sprinkle dry mixture over filling.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes or until top is no longer doughy.
Rotate dish every 4 minutes if no carousel.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: date cake with topping(microwave)
directions: Bake 6 to 8 minutes in microwave, turning every 1 1/2 minutes. Leave stand to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash according to directions.
Melt margarine and add stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Line bottom of 8-inch square baking dish with mixture, reserving 1/3 cup for topping.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle reserved topping over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: almond tea
directions: Steep tea in 2 cups boiling water for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and 2 1/2 quarts water in large container and bring to a boil. Add tea, almond extract, vanilla and fruit juices.
Serve hot. Yields 5 quarts.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
In mixing bowl, cream together shortening, sugar and eggs at medium speed until fluffy. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix at medium speed until combined.
Chill dough.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and then roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add rice; cook until browned. After rice is browned, add beef broth.
Cover pan and put in a 350° oven until tender (about 45 minutes).

title: microwaved scalloped potatoes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart bowl or dish combine potatoes and green pepper strips.
Cover.
Microwave on High 10 minutes, stir once.
Stir in soup.
Cover.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dorothy's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add vanilla and salt.
Keep beating and add the cream and milk.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: peanut butter dreams
directions: Cream margarine with brown sugar.
Add peanut butter, egg, vanilla and water.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in sifted flour and baking soda; stir in rolled oats.
Roll in balls, then sugar. Flatten slightly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shirley fromm's coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2/3 cup coconut, water and egg whites.
Beat for 2 minutes at high speed and 1 minute on low speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes.
Punch holes all over top with 2-pronged fork.
Pour cream of coconut over cake; let it cool.
Mix thawed Cool Whip and sour cream together; spread over cooled cake.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.
Can also be made with white cake mix.

title: make-a-mix dip
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Mix well; let dissolve. Add Bac*Os
before serving.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly
grease
9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over bottom.
Add
layer
of berries.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over them.
Spread
dry cake mix over all.
Drizzle margarine evenly over
cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Sprinkle on remaining sugar. Bake
at
350° for 25 minutes.
Take from oven and cut down center to
bottom
of pan to let juices rise.
Return to oven and continue to bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until top of cake is golden and crunchy.

title: chili pie
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups Fritos chips in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onions and half cheese over chips.
Pour heated Austex chili over onions and cheese.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Do not stir or toss.
Cover tightly overnight.
Toss with 1 cup Miracle Whip and 1/4 cup sugar just before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices of cookie dough.
Overlap edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate; carefully remove foil.
Turn right side up.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; mix well until blended.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit in design all over cream cheese.
Chill.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa in a pan.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
